 ('174', '4', '2', '1', 'en_us', '48', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Airbnb\",\"slug\":\"airbnb\",\"postDate\":1502508000,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#fd5b5b\",\"63\":[\"302\"],\"4\":\"<p><strong>The campaign that <em>\\u201c<\\/em><em>brought the house down<\\/em><em>\\u201d<\\/em>&nbsp;at <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/localhost:8888\\/bokeh\\/public_html\\/projects\\/airbnb#entry:4:url\\\">Airbnb<\\/a>.<\\/strong><\\/p>\",\"8\":\"center\",\"3\":[\"222\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"147\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>The Mission<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>On November 17, 2016, Airbnb announced the largest product expansion in its history. Just five weeks earlier, Bokeh was asked to join its sprint to the finish line.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Working alongside engineering, brand, product marketing, art, and C-level teams, we developed myriad content to educate users on new features, advertise and build awareness on social media, and, ultimately, to introduce the world to Airbnb Trips on-stage at Airbnb Open in Los Angeles.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"251\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>Services<\\/h2>\\r\\n<ul><li>Concept<\\/li><li>Branding Animation<\\/li><li>Film\\/Video<\\/li><li>Animation<\\/li><li>Digital Ads<\\/li><li>Social Ads<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"181\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"177\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"155\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>Let\\u2019s get functional<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>Humanity is a core component of the Airbnb brand. Every feature and service built into the new Airbnb app derives value from the way it connects to guests, hosts, and experiences. To reinforce this connection, we melded organic live-action footage with engaging UI animations and garnished it all with a touch of whimsy. The result was twelve functional product videos viewable in landscape and portrait mode.<\\/p>\"}},\"157\":{\"type\":\"videoCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":{\"158\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193177317\",\"caption\":\"Introducing Experiences\"}},\"159\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193177901\",\"caption\":\"Introducing Itinerary\"}},\"160\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193177150\",\"caption\":\"Introducing Co-hosting\"}},\"161\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193177011\",\"caption\":\"Introducing Social Impact Experiences\"}},\"280\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193176889\",\"caption\":\"Staying Connected in Cuba\"}}}}},\"164\":{\"type\":\"threeUpImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"firstImage\":[\"152\"],\"secondImage\":[\"21\"],\"thirdImage\":[\"72\"]}},\"146\":{\"type\":\"quote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"quote\":\"\\u201cThis film brought the house down. I cannot imagine now having done this without it.\\u201d\",\"avatar\":[\"250\"],\"personsName\":\"Brian Chesky\",\"jobTitle\":\"CEO of Airbnb\",\"shapeBackground\":[\"show\"]}},\"162\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>The Reveal<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>With two days before Airbnb Open, Brian needed a Hail Mary. He lacked a centerpiece for the launch announcement that firmly connected Airbnb\\u2019s digital product with the human experiences it fosters. So he asked us to apply our creative approach to the keynote anthem and make a film about the future of home sharing.<\\/p>\"}},\"153\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193175968\",\"caption\":\"Welcome to the World of Trips | Aired During Airbnb Open 2016 Keynote\"}},\"166\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193184792\",\"caption\":\"Airbnb Collections Teaser | Aired During AO 2016 Keynote\"}},\"165\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>Marketing Master Blaster<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>To build awareness, we applied this approach to four 15-second advertisements blasted across digital and social channels.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"167\":{\"type\":\"videoCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":{\"168\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/194444259\",\"caption\":\"Burlesque\"}},\"169\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193185940\",\"caption\":\"Samurai\"}},\"170\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193185835\",\"caption\":\"Runner\"}},\"171\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193186104\",\"caption\":\"Scenester\"}}}}},\"281\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>The bow on top<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>Every piece of content featured a reimagined Airbnb motion logo consistent with the fluid design aesthetic we developed for our animations.<\\/p>\"}},\"252\":{\"type\":\"twoUpImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"firstImage\":[\"29\"],\"secondImage\":[\"203\"]}},\"179\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>The payoff<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>The assets were leveraged across a variety of channels from Airbnb Open to product landing pages, social and YouTube, email newsletters, and paid media. The functional videos amassed over <strong>11 million views in less than three weeks<\\/strong>. On Airbnb product pages, the <strong>video click-through-rate reached as high as 15 percent<\\/strong>. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>We received coverage in the <strong><em>NYTimes<\\/em><\\/strong><strong>, Adweek, <\\/strong><strong><em>Travel + Leisure<\\/em><\\/strong><strong>, TechCrunch, Mashable, <\\/strong><strong><em>The Telegraph<\\/em><\\/strong><strong>, and Fast Company.<\\/strong><\\/p>\"}},\"180\":{\"type\":\"fiveUpImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"firstImage\":[\"199\"],\"secondImage\":[\"203\"],\"thirdImage\":[\"29\"],\"fourthImage\":[\"76\"],\"fifthImage\":[\"210\"]}}},\"2\":[\"96\"],\"9\":\"center\"}}', '2017-10-01 21:24:16', '2017-10-01 21:24:16', 'ad318716-bf28-42cf-b15f-e4d398decea5'),
