:\"clientLogo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"client\":[\"122\"]}},\"267\":{\"type\":\"clientLogo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"client\":[\"145\"]}},\"268\":{\"type\":\"clientLogo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"client\":[\"124\"]}},\"269\":{\"type\":\"clientLogo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"client\":[\"125\"]}},\"270\":{\"type\":\"clientLogo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"client\":[\"130\"]}},\"271\":{\"type\":\"clientLogo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"client\":[\"118\"]}},\"272\":{\"type\":\"clientLogo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"client\":[\"119\"]}},\"273\":{\"type\":\"clientLogo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"client\":[\"121\"]}},\"274\":{\"type\":\"clientLogo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"client\":[\"120\"]}}},\"6\":\"#e8930a\",\"38\":[\"4\",\"77\",\"28\"],\"3\":[\"247\"],\"59\":\"#f62944\",\"60\":\"#feae5a\",\"46\":{\"78\":{\"type\":\"offeredServices\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"serviceType\":\"Strategy\",\"service\":{\"79\":{\"type\":\"3\",\"fields\":{\"service\":\"Branding\"}},\"80\":{\"type\":\"3\",\"fields\":{\"service\":\"Content\"}},\"81\":{\"type\":\"3\",\"fields\":{\"service\":\"Social\"}},\"82\":{\"type\":\"3\",\"fields\":{\"service\":\"Digital\"}}}}},\"83\":{\"type\":\"offeredServices\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"serviceType\":\"Design\",\"service\":{\"84\":{\"type\":\"3\",\"fields\":{\"service\":\"Identity\"}},\"85\":{\"type\":\"3\",\"fields\":{\"service\":\"Style Guidelines\"}},\"86\":{\"type\":\"3\",\"fields\":{\"service\":\"Print\\/OOH\"}},\"87\":{\"type\":\"3\",\"fields\":{\"service\":\"UX\\/UI\"}}}}},\"88\":{\"type\":\"offeredServices\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"serviceType\":\"Content\",\"service\":{\"89\":{\"type\":\"3\",\"fields\":{\"service\":\"Film\\/Video\"}},\"90\":{\"type\":\"3\",\"fields\":{\"service\":\"Animation\"}},\"91\":{\"type\":\"3\",\"fields\":{\"service\":\"Product\\/Lifestyle Photography\"}},\"92\":{\"type\":\"3\",\"fields\":{\"service\":\"Copywriting\"}}}}}},\"40\":{\"93\":{\"type\":\"service\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copyLineOne\":\"We believe that open-hearted collaboration allows us to be in the right place to tell the right story on the channels that matter most.\",\"copyLineTwo\":\"That a unique balance of hunger and humility enables our imagination to be boundless.\",\"copyLineThree\":\"Bold, honest, and always capable, our ideas empower brands to speak with creativity and heart.\"}}},\"64\":{\"292\":{\"type\":\"textWithVideo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"How do we say our name? Is it:\",\"video\":[\"290\"]}},\"293\":{\"type\":\"textWithVideo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"Funnily enough, we don\'t know.\",\"video\":[\"286\"]}},\"294\":{\"type\":\"multiTextWithVideo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":{\"299\":{\"type\":\"4\",\"fields\":{\"line1\":\"David and doug went to film school.\",\"line2\":\"Sebastian went to business school.\",\"line3\":\"We all graduated with one goal: to create something awesome.\"}}},\"video\":[\"285\"]}},\"295\":{\"type\":\"textWithVideo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"So we started a business and made a pledge to never stop creating.\",\"video\":[\"287\"]}},\"296\":{\"type\":\"textWithVideo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"Little did we know where that would lead.\",\"video\":[\"289\"]}},\"297\":{\"type\":\"textWithVideo\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"The promise we made ourselves and our team is the promise we make you.\",\"video\":[\"291\"]}},\"298\":{\"type\":\"textWithVideoAndCta\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"Inspiration isn\'t static. It moves.\",\"video\":[\"288\"],\"cta\":{\"300\":{\"type\":\"5\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"Let\'s Ride\",\"ctaLink\":\"mailto:hello@seebokeh.com\"}}}}}},\"57\":{\"275\":{\"type\":\"word\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"word\":\"creative\"}},\"276\":{\"type\":\"word\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"word\":\"strategy\"}},\"277\":{\"type\":\"word\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"word\":\"design\"}},\"278\":{\"type\":\"word\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"word\":\"digital\"}}},\"62\":\"153553082\"}}', '2017-10-03 17:13:08', '2017-10-03 17:13:08', 'b3d40b9e-c3d8-43db-9574-a8a8e7fcf78f'),
 ('180', '279', '2', '75', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"The Irvine Company\",\"slug\":\"the-irvine-company\",\"postDate\":1506388860,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#ff8000\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p><strong>We made a video about real estate development exciting (Really.)<\\/strong><\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"206\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"316\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Mission:<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>In 2016, residential real estate development and master planning company the Irvine Company asked Bokeh to create a series of videos to generate community excitement and encourage the Cupertino City Council to approve its latest development, The Hamptons, located adjacent to Apple Park.<\\/p>\"}},\"new1\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Focus on What Really Matters<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Architects and developers aggrandizing another luxury development wasn\\u2019t going to resonate with anyone. In our interviews, we shifted the storytelling focus away from the specific design achievements of landscape architect Laurie Olin and architect Bernardo Fort-Brescia of Arquitectonica to how the development enriched the lives of its residents and the community of Cupertino as a whole. In other words, we felt the most effective approach would be to ground our story in humanity. <\\/p>\\r\\n\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>See the Unseen<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>To make a video for a development that didn\\u2019t exist yet, we partnered with the amazing creatives at Steelblue LLC to create 3D animated renderings of the complex with real and computer generated people in each space.&nbsp;<\\/p><p>First, they built out the CGI spaces with camera moves so we could make them consistent with the live-action shots. To make these homes feel active and alive, we asked Steelblue to fill up a green screen studio with a ton of extras. In fact, it was the most extras Steelblue had ever included in a single scene. It was also the first time they shot live extras swimming in a CGI pool. Using this combination of animation, interviews, aerial imagery, and B-roll footage, Bokeh made a real estate video with life and heart.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The cut-downs<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>It\\u2019s not easy to cover every detail of a multi-million dollar development in a single video. So we created a short series of topical cutdowns that highlighted The Hamptons\\u2019 most impressive features.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Hallelujah Housing<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The Hamptons passed the city council and the master plan was approved. Hallelujah! We have housing.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}},\"2\":[\"315\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-03 18:15:31', '2017-10-03 18:15:31', 'cd7c21a3-9144-4f29-a7ad-5218141fd245'),
 ('181', '77', '2', '75', 'en_us', '32', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"We backpacked around the globe to shoot a series for Instagram.\",\"slug\":\"instagram\",\"postDate\":1503364800,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#4463e4\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p><strong><strong>We backpacked around the globe to shoot a series for<\\/strong>&nbsp;<\\/strong><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bokeh.agency\\/projects\\/instagram#entry:77:url\\\"><\\/a><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bokeh.agency\\/projects\\/instagram#entry:77:url\\\">Instagram<\\/a>.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"center\",\"3\":[\"219\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"282\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>The Mission<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>In May 2016, Instagram asked Bokeh to develop the creative strategy behind its largest business marketing campaign. Over the next six months, Bokeh would trek across four continents and collaborate with twenty-four businesses in eight of Instagram\\u2019s top-performing markets to produce eight market-specific anthem films, one global anthem film, and two business profiles.<\\/p>\"}},\"283\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>Services<\\/h2>\\r\\n<ul><li>Concept<\\/li><li>Branding<\\/li><li>Film\\/Video<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"new1\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Nobody\\u2019s inspired by jargon<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Our creative approach was predicated on the belief that human connection is not driven by jargon or statistics. For a creative brand like Instagram, an emotional, relatable, &nbsp;and down-to-earth approach felt more powerful. Connection is not fostered by large, immobile production teams, so we strategized a plan that kept our footprint lean, our production value high, and placed a heavy value on agility. Then we tested this plan by developing a concept film and animatic.<\\/p>\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Non-stop<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Coordinating with teams around the world put the agency on a 24-hour schedule. At one point, Bokeh was filming in three countries simultaneously.<\\/p>\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Breaking the Rules<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>By keeping the creative and production light-on-its feet we kept ourselves open to be inspired by the businesses we profiled. For Dubai Tourism we invited our partner from Instagram on a whim to \\u201caccidently\\u201d skip an afternoon of video calls to ride ATVs into the Arabian desert. This allowed us to show Dubai as multi-faceted with both urban and natural landscapes. For Mercedes-Benz we figured a down-to-earth approach did no justice for their brand. We wanted to feel the speed and energy of their vehicles so we went out to their test track in Stuttgart, and up to the skies.<\\/p>\"}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The assets that we created were leveraged across a variety of channels, from keynote presentations to social and Vimeo, paid media, and the Instagram for Business blog.<\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"322\"],\"9\":\"bottom\"}}', '2017-10-03 18:18:52', '2017-10-03 18:18:52', '01231c32-3866-4231-b537-4d6c39d18d81'),
 ('182', '77', '2', '75', 'en_us', '33', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Instagram\",\"slug\":\"instagram\",\"postDate\":1503364800,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#4463e4\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p><strong><strong>We backpacked around the globe to shoot a series for<\\/strong>&nbsp;<\\/strong><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bokeh.agency\\/projects\\/instagram#entry:77:url\\\"><\\/a><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bokeh.agency\\/projects\\/instagram#entry:77:url\\\">Instagram<\\/a>.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"center\",\"3\":[\"219\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"282\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>The Mission<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>In May 2016, Instagram asked Bokeh to develop the creative strategy behind its largest business marketing campaign. Over the next six months, Bokeh would trek across four continents and collaborate with twenty-four businesses in eight of Instagram\\u2019s top-performing markets to produce eight market-specific anthem films, one global anthem film, and two business profiles.<\\/p>\"}},\"283\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>Services<\\/h2>\\r\\n<ul><li>Concept<\\/li><li>Branding<\\/li><li>Film\\/Video<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"323\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Nobody\\u2019s inspired by jargon<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Our creative approach was predicated on the belief that human connection is not driven by jargon or statistics. For a creative brand like Instagram, an emotional, relatable, &nbsp;and down-to-earth approach felt more powerful. Connection is not fostered by large, immobile production teams, so we strategized a plan that kept our footprint lean, our production value high, and placed a heavy value on agility. Then we tested this plan by developing a concept film and animatic.<\\/p>\"}},\"324\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Non-stop<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Coordinating with teams around the world put the agency on a 24-hour schedule. At one point, Bokeh was filming in three countries simultaneously.<\\/p>\"}},\"325\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Breaking the Rules<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>By keeping the creative and production light-on-its feet we kept ourselves open to be inspired by the businesses we profiled. For Dubai Tourism we invited our partner from Instagram on a whim to \\u201caccidently\\u201d skip an afternoon of video calls to ride ATVs into the Arabian desert. This allowed us to show Dubai as multi-faceted with both urban and natural landscapes. For Mercedes-Benz we figured a down-to-earth approach did no justice for their brand. We wanted to feel the speed and energy of their vehicles so we went out to their test track in Stuttgart, and up to the skies.<\\/p>\"}},\"326\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The assets that we created were leveraged across a variety of channels, from keynote presentations to social and Vimeo, paid media, and the Instagram for Business blog.<\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"322\"],\"9\":\"bottom\"}}', '2017-10-03 18:19:52', '2017-10-03 18:19:52', '9a472280-4a69-4c56-92f4-b93b014aa7ac'),
 ('183', '28', '2', '75', 'en_us', '29', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Philz Coffee\",\"slug\":\"philz-coffee\",\"postDate\":1502594280,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#00b4ae\",\"63\":[\"317\"],\"4\":\"<p>We cold called <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bokeh.agency\\/projects\\/philz-coffee#entry:28:url\\\">Philz Coffee<\\/a> to complain about their logo, and they let us do a rebrand.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"center\",\"3\":[\"57\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"32\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Bokeh took the unconventional approach of exploring Philz\\u2019s brand identity, refreshing it, and sending a new brand deck directly to Philz\\u2019s CEO, Jacob Jaber. With custom coffee blends and a customer experience like no other, we felt that Philz deserved a brand it could fully own. The plan worked! Throughout the course of 2016, Bokeh worked intimately with the Philz team to define a uniform brand strategy that would serve as a guide for future growth. <\\/p>\"}},\"new1\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Services<\\/h1>\\r\\n<ul><li>Workshops<\\/li><li>Strategy<\\/li><li>Design<\\/li><li>Brand Book & Guidelines<\\/li><\\/ul>\\r\\n\"}},\"35\":{\"type\":\"inlineImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"56\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Talk it Out<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Philz need a distinct vision, mission, and set of values that could be embraced internally and expressed in every decision they made. So we conducted individual interviews, a series of leadership workshops, and a company off-site to provide safe spaces to debate ideas and tinker with concepts. <\\/p>\\r\\n\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Trippin\\u2019 on research<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>White-space exercises and market research helped us create a profile for the typical Philz customer and to understand the perception of the Philz brand compared to that of its competitors. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Our research survey in San Francisco\\u2019s Bay Area, Los Angeles, and Washington, D.C. complemented the statistical analysis with in-person observations and on-site customer interviews.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}},\"33\":{\"type\":\"quote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"quote\":\"\\\"The depth of each slide is quite impressive and on-point. I appreciate your quick-wittedness, intuition and aesthetic\\u2026 I think you know us better than we know ourselves.\\\"\",\"avatar\":[\"57\"],\"personsName\":\"Jacob Jaber\",\"jobTitle\":\"CEO\",\"shapeBackground\":[\"show\"]}},\"34\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=wxLUj1Mrars\",\"caption\":\"Caption\"}},\"50\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The style guide<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p><i>Real<\\/i>, <i>warm<\\/i>, <i>undaunted<\\/i>, <i>relaxed<\\/i>, <i>neighborly<\\/i>, <i>light-hearted<\\/i>, and <i>unpretentious<\\/i> are the attributes infused throughout the new Philz brand identity. Starting with the logo and brand mark, we developed a custom system of colors, typography, illustrations, and iconography with guidelines.<\\/p>\"}},\"36\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"57\"],\"caption\":\"Coffee Beanz\"}},\"51\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Philz chose to pace the launch of the new branding by starting with in-store menus, wayfinding signage, and promotional newsletters.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}},\"2\":[\"314\"],\"9\":\"center\"}}', '2017-10-03 18:26:02', '2017-10-03 18:26:02', 'd1de97ce-8818-4e89-b2dc-46dd37d4d9ff'),
 ('184', '330', '2', '75', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Google Play\",\"slug\":\"google-play\",\"postDate\":1507055420,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#53f04f\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p>Our parents thought this Google Play April Fool\'s joke was real. Success!<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"246\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The team at Google Play was certain about two things. First, they wanted a video to commemorate the April Fool\\u2019s holiday. Second, they wanted the video to involve pets. With these parameters outlined, Bokeh went to work to develop a hilarious and entertaining video to introduce <i>Google Play for Pets<\\/i>.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Services<\\/h1><ul><li>Film\\/video<\\/li><li>Animation<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Make it believable<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>We made the conscious decision to avoid cheap laughs and cute gimmicks; to create an April Fool\\u2019s video that took itself and its intent to lead the audience astray seriously. The story&mdash;and the product at its center&mdash;had to be grounded in a real-world logic that the viewer could \\u201calmost\\u201d follow. We needed to develop a product idea that was simple, and solved a real human issue.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Our proposal: Google Play is introducing a new category of apps in the Play Store to help pet owners train their pets and keep them occupied while they\\u2019re away.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><\\/p>\"}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>With over 1.6M views across YouTube and Facebook, <i>Google Play for Pets <\\/i>was featured as one of the top April Fool\\u2019s pranks of 2017 by publications like <b>Adweek<\\/b> and <b>CNET<\\/b>.<\\/p>\"}},\"new5\":{\"type\":\"quote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"quote\":\"\\u201cyou guys are literally amazing - thank you for dealing w\\/ this crazy last minute madness.\\\"\",\"avatar\":\"\",\"personsName\":\"Meghan Lyons\",\"jobTitle\":\"Brand Marketing Manager, Google Play\",\"shapeBackground\":[\"show\"]}}},\"2\":[\"322\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-03 18:30:20', '2017-10-03 18:30:20', '8d84d552-1812-443a-83bc-cfd0a05ed1e1'),
 ('185', '336', '2', '75', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Airbnb & Easyjet\",\"slug\":\"airbnb-easyjet\",\"postDate\":1507055610,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#ff8000\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p><b><strong>Airbnb wanted a boarding pass passengers wouldn\\u2019t just throw away<\\/strong> \\ud83d\\ude10<\\/b><\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"97\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Airbnb noticed an interesting trend in Europe: A large percentage of Easyjet travellers are also avid Airbnb users. So in March 2017, Bokeh was asked to design a print ad to push Airbnb Experiences on the bottom third of all home-printed Easyjet boarding passes en route to Barcelona.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><\\/p>\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Make it Interactive<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The downside to boarding passes is that passengers just throw them away. For print-at-home boarding passes, little to no attention is paid to the lower quadrant of the page. Understandably, Airbnb did not want an ad with their logo to be ignored and dumped in the trash. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Our thought process was simple: For Easyjet passengers, the lack of seat-back entertainment means that there are limited ways to stay occupied during a flight. What might capture their attention? A game. By playing a game, the passengers entertain themselves for five minutes and Airbnb is given five minutes of their attention. We decided to pitch a crossword puzzle.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><\\/p>\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Keep it simple<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>We identified a list of words that related to Barcelona and some of the Experiences a traveller may partake in through Airbnb. We figured out how these words could fit together and came up with clues that were clever enough to keep the game fun, but easy enough to solve. (Safe to say, we went through many iterations.)<\\/p>\"}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The final ad ran on over 200,000 boarding passes for all Easyjet flights to Barcelona from continental Europe during March 2017. <\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}},\"2\":[\"313\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-03 18:33:30', '2017-10-03 18:33:30', '73dab9ce-84fe-4842-b876-e29f1388539b'),
 ('186', '341', '2', '75', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Google Maps\",\"slug\":\"google-maps\",\"postDate\":1507055848,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#62aee4\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p><b>The craziest damn video we\\u2019ve ever made for Google Maps in Turkey.<\\/b><\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"70\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>To announce the launch of Google Streetview and the Google Maps mobile application in Turkey, Bokeh was asked to produce an inspiring anthem video. However, there was one hurdle: No map data or Streetview imagery would be accessible. To be successful, our stylistic approach had to be less reliant on the availability of digital imagery and more attached to the target market\\u2019s culture.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Streetview minus the street view<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>How do you showcase a new feature without actually showing the feature? Establishing a partnership with DJI gave us the resources to shoot incredible aerial photography wherever we went. By combining this footage with hyperlapse photography and motion animation, we could mimic Satellite View in Google Maps and the user experience of moving between panoramas in Streetview.<\\/p>\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>From the Watchtower<br>We reached out to Leonardo Dalessandri, the Italian director of the short film <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/108018156\\\">Watchtower of Turkey<\\/a>. Watchtower captured the essence of Turkish culture; a balanced, artistic survey of Turkey\\u2019s people, customs, food, and landscapes. The video had amassed millions of views within Turkey, and from a marketing perspective incorporating Leo\\u2019s aesthetic would establish an immediate point-of-reference for users. The awe-inspiring, kinetically entrancing nature of the approach combined with Google\\u2019s reach could give the video virality.<\\/p>\"}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"quote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"quote\":\"\\\"This is super slick. Well done all around. Never seen anything quite like this\\u2026 The transitions between the various elements are so seamless.\\\"\",\"avatar\":\"\",\"personsName\":\"Gopal Shah\",\"jobTitle\":\"Product Manager, Google Earth\",\"shapeBackground\":[\"show\"]}},\"new5\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Hello Turkey<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Over the course of three weeks, we trekked across Istanbul and visited locales Izmir, Ephesus, \\u00c7e\\u015fme, and \\u015eirince.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"new6\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Perhaps the most incredibly cinematic and dynamic Google Maps launch video ever made suffered the most anticlimactic of fates. Never formally released due to the political climate in Turkey.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"322\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-03 18:37:28', '2017-10-03 18:37:28', 'a89e985a-5ef6-4d4c-bf7d-732d08d9ebd9'),
 ('187', '348', '2', '75', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Apple\",\"slug\":\"apple\",\"postDate\":1507055921,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#ae36ff\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p>We did something for Apple.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"117\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>That\\u2019s all we can say.<\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"322\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-03 18:38:41', '2017-10-03 18:38:41', 'e6a7f881-3130-4565-9e87-94823981d92c'),
 ('188', '351', '2', '75', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Google reCAPTCHA\",\"slug\":\"google-recaptcha\",\"postDate\":1507056071,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#f0eb15\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p>We turned boring technology into an exciting video for Google. Three times.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"223\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>To create and evolve a series of colorful, entertaining animated videos that could visualize Google\\u2019s reCAPTCHA, a technical online security product for verifying a user\\u2019s identity that\\u2019s engineered to be less noticeable.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><\\/p>\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Gotta CAPTCHA All<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>CAPTCHA is the virtual door that exists between you and the thing you really want to do&mdash;like make a safe and secure online purchase. But CAPTCHA lives completely in a digital world. We decided that an animated approach would be the easiest way to help people understand the technology. To keep things intelligible, but relatable, we borrowed the 8-bit Space Invader characters used on the reCAPTCHA website to represent malicious malware. We never gave them back&mdash;the Invaders became a major motif in the following videos. <\\/p>\\r\\n\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Nothing to See Here&hellip; No, Really.<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>For the second video, we were asked to visualize the concept of \\u201cinvisibility.\\u201d We brainstormed a little Rube Goldberg\\u2013esque machine to represent the complicated processes happening behind the scenes. Our motion designer, Tom, began exploring cute new ways to depict our pesky Invaders with antics like sneaking through an airport security line with a sweet \\u2018stache. A few cats started showing up as well, but that wasn\\u2019t exactly planned.<\\/p>\"}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>One More Time, with Feeling.<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Google asked us for a third video, but the only new thing was that reCAPTCHA was available on Android API. We took this as a creative challenge and pushed the animation by introducing new Invader shenanigans.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><\\/p>\"}},\"new5\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The videos received nearly 2.5 million views on YouTube. But our biggest gain was the creative latitude to develop and refine our animation skills.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"350\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-03 18:41:11', '2017-10-03 18:41:11', 'c4d09531-3750-4e50-9a1f-56825b179b6d'),
 ('189', '360', '2', '75', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Airbnb NYC Experiences\",\"slug\":\"airbnb-nyc-experiences\",\"postDate\":1507072535,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#ff4848\",\"63\":[\"357\"],\"4\":\"<p>Approved on a Friday. Organized on a Saturday. Took off on a Sunday. This is a marathon that was the launch of Airbnb Experiences in NYC.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"183\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Airbnb Experiences offers classes, tours, and other activities with locals to connect visitors with their surroundings in a fresh, meaningful way. Already live in a handful of cities, Airbnb asked Bokeh to produce the multichannel launch of Airbnb Experiences in New York. Bokeh had to wing it (literally) to the Big Apple to capture unique experiences in all five boroughs in just four days.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>To create the assets&mdash;videos, content copy, b2b, PR and social images&mdash;Bokeh took our coordination skills to new heights, not only working among Airbnb\\u2019s own art, PR, social, and marketing teams, but with photographers, videographers, and models to ensure seamless timing and transitioning.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><\\/p>\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Services<\\/h1>\\r\\n<ul><li>Film\\/video<\\/li><li>Photography<\\/li><li>Social<\\/li><li>Product<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>All Together Now<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>On the front end, we had to get all of the departments involved in the same room to identify individual needs and help convey the larger picture to everyone involved. After reviewing their wish lists, we consolidated them to create deliverables as smoothly and simultaneously as possible.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Then, we choreographed the production itself, prioritizing the anthem video but making sure that each photographer, videographer, and even \\u201ciPhoneagrapher\\u201d could get the shots needed fluidly and efficiently.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><\\/p>\"}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Empire State of Mind<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>For Airbnb Experiences New York, we wanted to ooze NYC vibes. We relied on bold cues, such as music and iconic New York scenes, but also incorporated a quick-cut editing style and, dynamic moving shots. To really hit that frenetic city pace, we centered the transitions on travel, including taxis, subways, and busy streets.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><\\/p>\"}},\"new5\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\"}}},\"2\":[\"322\",\"358\",\"359\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-03 23:15:36', '2017-10-03 23:15:36', '6c445c53-2a71-4b02-8c9a-2898cbf86f2e'),
