:{\"type\":\"videoCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":{\"158\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193177317\",\"caption\":\"Introducing Experiences\"}},\"159\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193177901\",\"caption\":\"Introducing Itinerary\"}},\"160\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193177150\",\"caption\":\"Introducing Co-hosting\"}},\"161\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193177011\",\"caption\":\"Introducing Social Impact Experiences\"}},\"280\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193176889\",\"caption\":\"Staying Connected in Cuba\"}}}}},\"146\":{\"type\":\"quote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"quote\":\"\\u201cThis film brought the house down. I cannot imagine now having done this without it.\\u201d\",\"avatar\":[\"250\"],\"personsName\":\"Brian Chesky\",\"jobTitle\":\"CEO of Airbnb\",\"shapeBackground\":[\"show\"]}},\"162\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>The Reveal<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>With two days before Airbnb Open, Brian needed a Hail Mary. He lacked a centerpiece for the launch announcement that firmly connected Airbnb\\u2019s digital product with the human experiences it fosters. So he asked us to apply our creative approach to the keynote anthem and make a film about the future of home sharing.<\\/p>\"}},\"153\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193175968\",\"caption\":\"Welcome to the World of Trips | Aired During Airbnb Open 2016 Keynote\"}},\"166\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193184792\",\"caption\":\"Airbnb Collections Teaser | Aired During AO 2016 Keynote\"}},\"165\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>Marketing Master Blaster<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>To build awareness, we applied this approach to four 15-second advertisements blasted across digital and social channels.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"167\":{\"type\":\"videoCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":{\"168\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/194444259\",\"caption\":\"Burlesque\"}},\"169\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193185940\",\"caption\":\"Samurai\"}},\"170\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193185835\",\"caption\":\"Runner\"}},\"171\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193186104\",\"caption\":\"Scenester\"}}}}},\"281\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>The bow on top<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>Every piece of content featured a reimagined Airbnb motion logo consistent with the fluid design aesthetic we developed for our animations.<\\/p>\"}},\"667\":{\"type\":\"inlineImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"666\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"179\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>The payoff<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>The assets were leveraged across a variety of channels from Airbnb Open to product landing pages, social and YouTube, email newsletters, and paid media. The functional videos amassed over <strong>11 million views<\\/strong><strong> in less than three weeks<\\/strong>. On Airbnb product pages, the <strong>video click-through-rate reached as high as 15 percent<\\/strong>. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>We received coverage in the <strong><em>NYTimes<\\/em><\\/strong><strong>, Adweek, <\\/strong><strong><em>Travel + Leisure<\\/em><\\/strong><strong>, TechCrunch, Mashable, <\\/strong><strong><em>The Telegraph<\\/em><\\/strong><strong>, and Fast Company.<\\/strong><\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"96\"],\"9\":\"center\"}}', '2017-10-06 22:56:37', '2017-10-06 22:56:37', '0c81123b-3ab3-4356-9cd9-858f2f8b48a7'),
 ('275', '336', '2', '75', 'en_us', '7', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Airbnb & Easyjet\",\"slug\":\"airbnb-easyjet\",\"postDate\":1507055580,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#fc4f09\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p><strong><strong>Airbnb wanted a boarding pass passengers wouldn\\u2019t just throw away<\\/strong><\\/strong><\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"663\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"337\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Airbnb noticed an interesting trend in Europe: A large percentage of Easyjet travellers are also avid Airbnb users. So in March 2017, Bokeh was asked to design a print ad to push Airbnb Experiences on the bottom third of all home-printed Easyjet boarding passes en route to Barcelona.<\\/p>\"}},\"339\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Keep it simple<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>We identified a list of words that related to Barcelona and some of the Experiences a traveller may partake in through Airbnb. We figured out how these words could fit together and came up with clues that were clever enough to keep the game fun, but easy enough to solve. (Safe to say, we went through many iterations.)<\\/p>\"}},\"628\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"626\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"338\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Make it Interactive<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The downside to boarding passes is that passengers just throw them away. For print-at-home boarding passes, little to no attention is paid to the lower quadrant of the page. Understandably, Airbnb did not want an ad with their logo to be ignored and dumped in the trash. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Our thought process was simple: For Easyjet passengers, the lack of seat-back entertainment means that there are limited ways to stay occupied during a flight. What might capture their attention? A game. By playing a game, the passengers entertain themselves for five minutes and Airbnb is given five minutes of their attention. We decided to pitch a crossword puzzle.<\\/p>\"}},\"340\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The final ad ran on over 200,000 boarding passes for all Easyjet flights to Barcelona from continental Europe during March 2017. <\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"313\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-06 22:57:43', '2017-10-06 22:57:43', 'bb8035c1-f59e-4dd6-be2e-151e1d18a02f'),
 ('276', '279', '2', '75', 'en_us', '10', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"The Irvine Company\",\"slug\":\"the-irvine-company\",\"postDate\":1506388860,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#b536f9\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p><strong>We made a video about real estate development exciting (Really.)<\\/strong><\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"564\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"316\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Mission:<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>In 2016, residential real estate development and master planning company the Irvine Company asked Bokeh to create a series of videos to generate community excitement and encourage the Cupertino City Council to approve its latest development, The Hamptons, located adjacent to Apple Park.<\\/p>\"}},\"571\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/171478246\",\"caption\":\"The Hamptons, Cupertino\"}},\"318\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Focus on What Really Matters<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Architects and developers aggrandizing another luxury development wasn\\u2019t going to resonate with anyone. In our interviews, we shifted the storytelling focus away from the specific design achievements of landscape architect Laurie Olin and architect Bernardo Fort-Brescia of Arquitectonica to how the development enriched the lives of its residents and the community of Cupertino as a whole. In other words, we felt the most effective approach would be to ground our story in humanity. <\\/p>\"}},\"572\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"573\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"565\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"574\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"567\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"575\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"568\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"576\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"564\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"633\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"630\"],\"caption\":\"\"}}}}},\"319\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>See the Unseen<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>To make a video for a development that didn\\u2019t exist yet, we partnered with the amazing creatives at Steelblue LLC to create 3D animated renderings of the complex with real and computer generated people in each space.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>First, they built out the CGI spaces with camera moves so we could make them consistent with the live-action shots. To make these homes feel active and alive, we asked Steelblue to fill up a green screen studio with a ton of extras. In fact, it was the most extras Steelblue had ever included in a single scene. It was also the first time they shot live extras swimming in a CGI pool. Using this combination of animation, interviews, aerial imagery, and B-roll footage, Bokeh made a real estate video with life and heart.<\\/p>\"}},\"320\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The cut-downs<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>It\\u2019s not easy to cover every detail of a multi-million dollar development in a single video. So we created a short series of topical cutdowns that highlighted The Hamptons\\u2019 most impressive features.<\\/p>\"}},\"578\":{\"type\":\"videoCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":{\"579\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/168412289\",\"caption\":\"Sustainability\"}},\"580\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/168412287\",\"caption\":\"Planning Principles\"}},\"581\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/168412286\",\"caption\":\"Public Promenade\"}},\"582\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/168412285\",\"caption\":\"Building Composition\"}},\"583\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/168412284\",\"caption\":\"Perimeter Trail\"}},\"584\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/168412279\",\"caption\":\"Landscape\"}}}}},\"321\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Hallelujah Housing<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The Hamptons passed the city council and the master plan was approved. Hallelujah! We have housing.<\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"315\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-06 22:58:18', '2017-10-06 22:58:18', '6db2bcf7-b672-4b6b-ad23-685a0868e1cd'),
 ('277', '341', '2', '75', 'en_us', '8', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Google Maps\",\"slug\":\"google-maps\",\"postDate\":1507055820,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#ffbf00\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p><strong>The craziest damn video we\\u2019ve ever made for Google Maps in Turkey.<\\/strong><\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"548\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"342\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>To announce the launch of Google Streetview and the Google Maps mobile application in Turkey, Bokeh was asked to produce an inspiring anthem video. However, there was one hurdle: No map data or Streetview imagery would be accessible. To be successful, our stylistic approach had to be less reliant on the availability of digital imagery and more attached to the target market\\u2019s culture.<\\/p>\"}},\"554\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/130380842\",\"caption\":\"Google Maps: Hello Turkey\"}},\"343\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Streetview minus the street view<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>How do you showcase a new feature without actually showing the feature? Establishing a partnership with DJI gave us the resources to shoot incredible aerial photography wherever we went. By combining this footage with hyperlapse photography and motion animation, we could mimic Satellite View in Google Maps and the user experience of moving between panoramas in Streetview.<\\/p>\"}},\"577\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/118982276\",\"caption\":\"Inspired by the DJI Inspire\"}},\"344\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>From the Watchtower<br>We reached out to Leonardo Dalessandri, the Italian director of the short film <a href=\\\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/108018156\\\">Watchtower of Turkey<\\/a>. Watchtower captured the essence of Turkish culture; a balanced, artistic survey of Turkey\\u2019s people, customs, food, and landscapes. The video had amassed millions of views within Turkey, and from a marketing perspective incorporating Leo\\u2019s aesthetic would establish an immediate point-of-reference for users. The awe-inspiring, kinetically entrancing nature of the approach combined with Google\\u2019s reach could give the video virality.<\\/p>\"}},\"555\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"558\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"542\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"557\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"549\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"559\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"544\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"560\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"545\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"561\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"552\"],\"caption\":\"\"}}}}},\"345\":{\"type\":\"quote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"quote\":\"\\\"This is super slick. Well done all around. Never seen anything quite like this\\u2026 The transitions between the various elements are so seamless.\\\"\",\"avatar\":\"\",\"personsName\":\"Gopal Shah\",\"jobTitle\":\"Product Manager, Google Earth\",\"shapeBackground\":[\"show\"]}},\"346\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Hello Turkey<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Over the course of three weeks, we trekked across Istanbul and visited locales Izmir, Ephesus, \\u00c7e\\u015fme, and \\u015eirince.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"562\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"543\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"347\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Perhaps the most incredibly cinematic and dynamic Google Maps launch video ever made suffered the most anticlimactic of fates. Never formally released due to the political climate in Turkey.<\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"322\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-06 22:58:56', '2017-10-06 22:58:56', 'a7329368-34b5-40c9-a4a3-69023e7f8bc1'),
 ('278', '351', '2', '75', 'en_us', '10', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Google reCAPTCHA\",\"slug\":\"google-recaptcha\",\"postDate\":1507056060,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#2dbc45\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p>We turned boring technology into an exciting video for Google. Three times.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"585\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"352\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>To create and evolve a series of colorful, entertaining animated videos that could visualize Google\\u2019s reCAPTCHA, a technical online security product for verifying a user\\u2019s identity that\\u2019s engineered to be less noticeable.<\\/p>\"}},\"534\":{\"type\":\"inlineImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"537\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"353\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Gotta CAPTCHA All<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>CAPTCHA is the virtual door that exists between you and the thing you really want to do&mdash;like make a safe and secure online purchase. But CAPTCHA lives completely in a digital world. We decided that an animated approach would be the easiest way to help people understand the technology. To keep things intelligible, but relatable, we borrowed the 8-bit Space Invader characters used on the reCAPTCHA website to represent malicious malware. We never gave them back&mdash;the Invaders became a major motif in the following videos. <\\/p>\"}},\"528\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/113330383\",\"caption\":\"Introducing the no CAPTCHA reCAPTCHA\"}},\"354\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Nothing to See Here&hellip; No, Really.<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>For the second video, we were asked to visualize the concept of \\u201cinvisibility.\\u201d We brainstormed a little Rube Goldberg\\u2013esque machine to represent the complicated processes happening behind the scenes. Our motion designer, Tom, began exploring cute new ways to depict our pesky Invaders with antics like sneaking through an airport security line with a sweet \\u2018stache. A few cats started showing up as well, but that wasn\\u2019t exactly planned.<\\/p>\"}},\"529\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/166595260\",\"caption\":\"reCAPTCHA: Tough on Bots, Easy on Humans\"}},\"355\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>One More Time, with Feeling.<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Google asked us for a third video, but the only new thing was that reCAPTCHA was available on Android API. We took this as a creative challenge and pushed the animation by introducing new Invader shenanigans.<\\/p>\"}},\"530\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/221336511\",\"caption\":\"Introducing the reCAPTCHA Android API\"}},\"356\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The videos received nearly 2.5 million views on YouTube. But our biggest gain was the creative latitude to develop and refine our animation skills.<\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"350\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-06 23:00:03', '2017-10-06 23:00:03', '1b661e14-26d8-4a9f-8a34-d289fe98e475'),
 ('279', '330', '2', '75', 'en_us', '6', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Google Play\",\"slug\":\"google-play\",\"postDate\":1507055400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#2dbc45\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p>Our parents thought this Google Play April Fool\'s joke was real. Success!<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"653\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"331\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The team at Google Play was certain about two things. First, they wanted a video to commemorate the April Fool\\u2019s holiday. Second, they wanted the video to involve pets. With these parameters outlined, Bokeh went to work to develop a hilarious and entertaining video to introduce <em>Google Play for Pets<\\/em>.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"332\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Services<\\/h1>\\r\\n<ul><li>Film\\/video<\\/li><li>Animation<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"654\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/213573065\",\"caption\":\"Google Play for Pets\"}},\"333\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Make it believable<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>We made the conscious decision to avoid cheap laughs and cute gimmicks; to create an April Fool\\u2019s video that took itself and its intent to lead the audience astray seriously. The story&mdash;and the product at its center&mdash;had to be grounded in a real-world logic that the viewer could \\u201calmost\\u201d follow. We needed to develop a product idea that was simple, and solved a real human issue.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Our proposal: Google Play is introducing a new category of apps in the Play Store to help pet owners train their pets and keep them occupied while they\\u2019re away.<\\/p>\"}},\"655\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"658\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"644\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"657\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"634\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"659\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"643\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"661\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"635\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"662\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"651\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"656\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"641\"],\"caption\":\"\"}}}}},\"334\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>With over 1.6M views across YouTube and Facebook, <em>Google Play for Pets <\\/em>was featured as one of the top April Fool\\u2019s pranks of 2017 by publications like <strong>Adweek<\\/strong> and <strong>CNET<\\/strong>.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\"}},\"335\":{\"type\":\"quote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"quote\":\"\\u201cyou guys are literally amazing - thank you for dealing w\\/ this crazy last minute madness.\\\"\",\"avatar\":\"\",\"personsName\":\"Meghan Lyons\",\"jobTitle\":\"Brand Marketing Manager, Google Play\",\"shapeBackground\":[\"show\"]}}},\"2\":[\"322\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-06 23:00:20', '2017-10-06 23:00:20', '27fcbe09-3aba-407b-9dca-e228b8a7cba2'),
 ('280', '360', '2', '75', 'en_us', '23', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Airbnb NYC Experiences\",\"slug\":\"airbnb-nyc-experiences\",\"postDate\":1507072500,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#ff4848\",\"63\":[\"302\"],\"4\":\"<p>Approved Friday, organized Saturday, took off Sunday. That was&nbsp;<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bokeh.agency\\/projects\\/airbnb-nyc-experiences#entry:360:url\\\">Airbnb Experiences<\\/a>&nbsp;NYC.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"372\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"361\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Airbnb Experiences offers classes, tours, and other activities with locals to connect visitors with their surroundings in a fresh, meaningful way. Already live in a handful of cities, Airbnb asked Bokeh to produce the multichannel launch of Airbnb Experiences in New York. Bokeh had to wing it (literally) to the Big Apple to capture unique experiences in all five boroughs in just four days.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>To create the assets&mdash;videos, content copy, b2b, PR and social images&mdash;Bokeh took our coordination skills to new heights, not only working among Airbnb\\u2019s own art, PR, social, and marketing teams, but with photographers, videographers, and models to ensure seamless timing and transitioning.<\\/p>\"}},\"362\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Services<\\/h1>\\r\\n<ul><li>Film\\/Video<\\/li><li>Photography<\\/li><li>Social<\\/li><li>Product<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"409\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/235420494\",\"caption\":\"\"}},\"363\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>All Together Now<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>On the front end, we had to get all of the departments involved in the same room to identify individual needs and help convey the larger picture to everyone involved. After reviewing their wish lists, we consolidated them to create deliverables as smoothly and simultaneously as possible.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Then, we choreographed the production itself, prioritizing the anthem video but making sure that each photographer, videographer, and even \\u201ciPhoneagrapher\\u201d could get the shots needed fluidly and efficiently.<\\/p>\"}},\"421\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"418\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"364\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Empire State of Mind<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>For Airbnb Experiences New York, we wanted to ooze NYC vibes. We relied on bold cues, such as music and iconic New York scenes, but also incorporated a quick-cut editing style and, dynamic moving shots. To really hit that frenetic city pace, we centered the transitions on travel, including taxis, subways, and busy streets.<\\/p>\"}},\"411\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"412\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"378\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Harvest Honey with Asher\\\" Experience\"}},\"420\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"376\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Harvest Honey with Asher\\\" Experience\"}},\"413\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"381\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Be Greek with Angelis\\\" Experience\"}},\"423\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"383\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Be Greek with Angelis\\\" Experience\"}},\"422\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"395\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Design Jewelry with Dynasty and Soull\\\" Experience\"}},\"414\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"398\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Design Jewelry with Dynasty and Soull\\\" Experience\"}},\"415\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"402\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Design Jewelry with Dynasty and Soull\\\" Experience\"}},\"416\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"391\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Make a Hat with Brandon\\\" Experience\"}},\"427\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"394\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Make a Hat with Brandon\\\" Experience\"}},\"429\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"388\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Street Dance with It\'s Showtime NYC!\\\" Experience\"}},\"424\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"407\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Sail NYC History with Matt\\\" Experience\"}},\"430\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"404\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Sail NYC History with Matt\\\" Experience\"}}}}},\"365\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\"}},\"428\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"426\"],\"caption\":\"\"}}},\"2\":[\"322\",\"358\",\"359\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-06 23:01:05', '2017-10-06 23:01:05', '2aeca8e3-d2c1-4e39-b8fc-50f4c1317cae'),
