 ('304', '279', '2', '1', 'en_us', '11', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"The Irvine Company\",\"slug\":\"the-irvine-company\",\"postDate\":1506388860,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#b536f9\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p><strong>We made a video about real estate development exciting (Really.)<\\/strong><\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"564\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"316\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Mission:<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>In 2016, residential real estate development and master planning company the Irvine Company asked Bokeh to create a series of videos to generate community excitement and encourage the Cupertino City Council to approve its latest development, The Hamptons, located adjacent to Apple Park.<\\/p>\"}},\"571\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/171478246\",\"caption\":\"The Hamptons, Cupertino\",\"ratio\":\"235-1\"}},\"318\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Focus on What Really Matters<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Architects and developers aggrandizing another luxury development wasn\\u2019t going to resonate with anyone. In our interviews, we shifted the storytelling focus away from the specific design achievements of landscape architect Laurie Olin and architect Bernardo Fort-Brescia of Arquitectonica to how the development enriched the lives of its residents and the community of Cupertino as a whole. In other words, we felt the most effective approach would be to ground our story in humanity. <\\/p>\"}},\"572\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"573\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"565\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"574\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"567\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"575\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"568\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"576\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"564\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"633\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"630\"],\"caption\":\"\"}}}}},\"319\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>See the Unseen<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>To make a video for a development that didn\\u2019t exist yet, we partnered with the amazing creatives at Steelblue LLC to create 3D animated renderings of the complex with real and computer generated people in each space.&nbsp;<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>First, they built out the CGI spaces with camera moves so we could make them consistent with the live-action shots. To make these homes feel active and alive, we asked Steelblue to fill up a green screen studio with a ton of extras. In fact, it was the most extras Steelblue had ever included in a single scene. It was also the first time they shot live extras swimming in a CGI pool. Using this combination of animation, interviews, aerial imagery, and B-roll footage, Bokeh made a real estate video with life and heart.<\\/p>\"}},\"320\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The cut-downs<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>It\\u2019s not easy to cover every detail of a multi-million dollar development in a single video. So we created a short series of topical cutdowns that highlighted The Hamptons\\u2019 most impressive features.<\\/p>\"}},\"578\":{\"type\":\"videoCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":{\"579\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/168412289\",\"caption\":\"Sustainability\"}},\"580\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/168412287\",\"caption\":\"Planning Principles\"}},\"581\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/168412286\",\"caption\":\"Public Promenade\"}},\"582\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/168412285\",\"caption\":\"Building Composition\"}},\"583\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/168412284\",\"caption\":\"Perimeter Trail\"}},\"584\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/168412279\",\"caption\":\"Landscape\"}}}}},\"321\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Hallelujah Housing<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The Hamptons passed the city council and the master plan was approved. Hallelujah! We have housing.<\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"315\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-07 01:36:50', '2017-10-07 01:36:50', 'bf35d48f-2ce3-443f-aba9-9760e7f04fc0'),
 ('305', '348', '2', '1', 'en_us', '8', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Apple\",\"slug\":\"apple\",\"postDate\":1507055880,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#91bfff\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p>We did something for Apple.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"586\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"540\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"541\"],\"caption\":\"\"}}},\"2\":[\"322\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-07 01:40:50', '2017-10-07 01:40:50', '06e9ad29-a602-41ee-828d-574377387f03'),
 ('306', '367', '2', '1', 'en_us', '11', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Airbnb & Resy\",\"slug\":\"airbnb-resy\",\"postDate\":1507072860,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#0d6774\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p>We created a video to announce the launch of Resy on Airbnb\\u2019s app, but still had to make our own reservations.&nbsp;\\ud83d\\udc96<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"509\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"368\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>As part of its goal to make Airbnb a more functional app for users while they are on their trip, Airbnb partnered with Resy, a restaurant-reservation service that offers users a curated list of options&mdash;avoiding the inconvenience of having to find good food on a trip. Airbnb asked Bokeh to develop a video to announce the launch of its collaboration with Resy to offer instant restaurant reservations through the Airbnb app.<\\/p>\"}},\"524\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"522\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"515\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"516\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"511\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"525\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"510\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"517\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"509\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"518\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"508\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"519\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"507\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"520\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"506\"],\"caption\":\"\"}}}}},\"369\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>You Know Me, The OG<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Taking advantage of the open ended creative, we wanted to explore integrating the photorealistic UI of the product into the illustrated animation. To integrate the video with the design even further, we based our color palette around green and yellow, the colors used in the app. For the animated portion, we brought in Swedish illustrator Jonas Mosesson, who basically invented the graphic aesthetic we wanted to deploy. Rather than hire someone to imitate someone else, we\\u2019ve found that the best, most efficient way to capture a distinct style is to bring in the person who created it. The resulting illustrations he did trended on Dribble\\u2019s home page for several days.<\\/p>\"}},\"370\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Where\\u2019s Bokeh?<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Although the video was simple, we were able to include a few Easter eggs into the design, such as including our producer\\u2019s name as one of the restaurants offered.<\\/p>\"}},\"514\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/234724566\",\"caption\":\"\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"371\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\"}}},\"2\":[\"350\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-07 01:51:37', '2017-10-07 01:51:37', 'd468af9d-b103-4141-96c7-c57ed1030e41'),
