 ('314', '367', '2', '75', 'en_us', '15', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Airbnb & Resy\",\"slug\":\"airbnb-resy\",\"postDate\":1507072860,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#0d6774\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p>We created a video to announce the launch of Resy on Airbnb\\u2019s app, but still had to make our own reservations.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"509\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"368\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>As part of its goal to make Airbnb a more functional app for users while they are on their trip, Airbnb partnered with Resy, a restaurant-reservation service that offers users a curated list of options&mdash;avoiding the inconvenience of having to find good food on a trip. Airbnb asked Bokeh to develop a video to announce the launch of its collaboration with Resy to offer instant restaurant reservations through the Airbnb app.<\\/p>\"}},\"524\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"695\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"369\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>You Know Me, The OG<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Taking advantage of the open ended creative, we wanted to explore integrating the photorealistic UI of the product into the illustrated animation. To integrate the video with the design even further, we based our color palette around green and yellow, the colors used in the app. For the animated portion, we brought in Swedish illustrator Jonas Mosesson, who basically invented the graphic aesthetic we wanted to deploy. Rather than hire someone to imitate someone else, we\\u2019ve found that the best, most efficient way to capture a distinct style is to bring in the person who created it. The resulting illustrations he did trended on Dribble\\u2019s home page for several days.<\\/p>\"}},\"515\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"516\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"511\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"525\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"510\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"517\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"509\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"518\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"508\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"519\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"507\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"520\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"506\"],\"caption\":\"\"}}}}},\"370\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Where\\u2019s Bokeh?<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Although the video was simple, we were able to include a few Easter eggs into the design, such as including our producer\\u2019s name as one of the restaurants offered.<\\/p>\"}},\"514\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/234724566\",\"caption\":\"\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"371\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\"}}},\"2\":[\"350\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-07 04:20:53', '2017-10-07 04:20:53', '7edf29c7-08a0-4b34-b10d-6bf99587f1f9'),
 ('315', '4', '2', '75', 'en_us', '53', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Airbnb World of Trips\",\"slug\":\"airbnb\",\"postDate\":1502508000,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#ff4848\",\"63\":[\"302\"],\"4\":\"<p><strong>The campaign that <em>\\u201c<\\/em><em>brought the house down<\\/em><em>\\u201d<\\/em>&nbsp;at <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bokeh.agency\\/projects\\/airbnb#entry:4:url\\\">Airbnb<\\/a>.<\\/strong><\\/p>\",\"8\":\"center\",\"3\":[\"222\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"147\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>The Mission<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>On November 17, 2016, Airbnb announced the largest product expansion in its history. Just five weeks earlier, Bokeh was asked to join its sprint to the finish line.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Working alongside engineering, brand, product marketing, art, and C-level teams, we developed myriad content to educate users on new features, advertise and build awareness on social media, and, ultimately, to introduce the world to Airbnb Trips on-stage at Airbnb Open in Los Angeles.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"251\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>Services<\\/h2>\\r\\n<ul><li>Concept<\\/li><li>Branding Animation<\\/li><li>Film\\/Video<\\/li><li>Animation<\\/li><li>Digital Ads<\\/li><li>Social Ads<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"181\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"177\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"155\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>Let\\u2019s get functional<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>Humanity is a core component of the Airbnb brand. Every feature and service built into the new Airbnb app derives value from the way it connects to guests, hosts, and experiences. To reinforce this connection, we melded organic live-action footage with engaging UI animations and garnished it all with a touch of whimsy. The result was twelve functional product videos viewable in landscape and portrait mode.<\\/p>\"}},\"157\":{\"type\":\"videoCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":{\"158\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193177317\",\"caption\":\"Introducing Experiences\"}},\"159\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193177901\",\"caption\":\"Introducing Itinerary\"}},\"160\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193177150\",\"caption\":\"Introducing Co-hosting\"}},\"161\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193177011\",\"caption\":\"Introducing Social Impact Experiences\"}},\"280\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193176889\",\"caption\":\"Staying Connected in Cuba\"}}}}},\"146\":{\"type\":\"quote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"quote\":\"\\u201cThis film brought the house down. I cannot imagine now having done this without it.\\u201d\",\"avatar\":[\"250\"],\"personsName\":\"Brian Chesky\",\"jobTitle\":\"CEO of Airbnb\",\"shapeBackground\":[\"show\"]}},\"162\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>The Reveal<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>With two days before Airbnb Open, Brian needed a Hail Mary. He lacked a centerpiece for the launch announcement that firmly connected Airbnb\\u2019s digital product with the human experiences it fosters. So he asked us to apply our creative approach to the keynote anthem and make a film about the future of home sharing.<\\/p>\"}},\"153\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193175968\",\"caption\":\"Welcome to the World of Trips | Aired During Airbnb Open 2016 Keynote\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"166\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193184792\",\"caption\":\"Airbnb Collections Teaser | Aired During AO 2016 Keynote\",\"ratio\":\"235-1\"}},\"165\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>Marketing Master Blaster<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>To build awareness, we applied this approach to four 15-second advertisements blasted across digital and social channels.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"167\":{\"type\":\"videoCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":{\"168\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/194444259\",\"caption\":\"Burlesque\"}},\"169\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193185940\",\"caption\":\"Samurai\"}},\"170\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193185835\",\"caption\":\"Runner\"}},\"171\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193186104\",\"caption\":\"Scenester\"}}}}},\"281\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>The bow on top<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>Every piece of content featured a reimagined Airbnb motion logo consistent with the fluid design aesthetic we developed for our animations.<\\/p>\"}},\"667\":{\"type\":\"inlineImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"666\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"179\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>The payoff<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>The assets were leveraged across a variety of channels from Airbnb Open to product landing pages, social and YouTube, email newsletters, and paid media. The functional videos amassed over <strong>11 million views<\\/strong><strong> in less than three weeks<\\/strong>. On Airbnb product pages, the <strong>video click-through-rate reached as high as 15 percent<\\/strong>. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>We received coverage in the <strong><em>NYTimes<\\/em><\\/strong><strong>, Adweek, <\\/strong><strong><em>Travel + Leisure<\\/em><\\/strong><strong>, TechCrunch, Mashable, <\\/strong><strong><em>The Telegraph<\\/em><\\/strong><strong>, and Fast Company.<\\/strong><\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"96\"],\"9\":\"center\"}}', '2017-10-07 04:27:45', '2017-10-07 04:27:45', '6151d0fe-292f-42b7-a30c-b057a361b2df'),
 ('316', '330', '2', '75', 'en_us', '7', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Google Play\",\"slug\":\"google-play\",\"postDate\":1507055400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#2dbc45\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p>Our parents thought this Google Play April Fool\'s joke was real. Success!<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"696\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"331\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The team at Google Play was certain about two things. First, they wanted a video to commemorate the April Fool\\u2019s holiday. Second, they wanted the video to involve pets. With these parameters outlined, Bokeh went to work to develop a hilarious and entertaining video to introduce <em>Google Play for Pets<\\/em>.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"332\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Services<\\/h1>\\r\\n<ul><li>Film\\/video<\\/li><li>Animation<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"654\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/213573065\",\"caption\":\"Google Play for Pets\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"333\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Make it believable<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>We made the conscious decision to avoid cheap laughs and cute gimmicks; to create an April Fool\\u2019s video that took itself and its intent to lead the audience astray seriously. The story&mdash;and the product at its center&mdash;had to be grounded in a real-world logic that the viewer could \\u201calmost\\u201d follow. We needed to develop a product idea that was simple, and solved a real human issue.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Our proposal: Google Play is introducing a new category of apps in the Play Store to help pet owners train their pets and keep them occupied while they\\u2019re away.<\\/p>\"}},\"655\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"658\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"644\"],\"caption\":\"