 ('373', '351', '2', '75', 'en_us', '12', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Google reCAPTCHA\",\"slug\":\"google-recaptcha\",\"postDate\":1507056060,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#42e161\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p>We found a way to make Google security software adorable. Three times.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"585\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"352\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>To create and evolve a series of colorful, entertaining animated videos that could visualize Google\\u2019s reCAPTCHA, a technical online security product for verifying a user\\u2019s identity that\\u2019s engineered to be less noticeable.<\\/p>\"}},\"534\":{\"type\":\"inlineImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"537\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"353\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Gotta CAPTCHA All<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>CAPTCHA is the virtual door that exists between you and the thing you really want to do&mdash;like make a safe and secure online purchase. But CAPTCHA lives completely in a digital world. We decided that an animated approach would be the easiest way to help people understand the technology. To keep things intelligible, but relatable, we borrowed the 8-bit Space Invader characters used on the reCAPTCHA website to represent malicious malware. We never gave them back&mdash;the Invaders became a major motif in the following videos. <\\/p>\"}},\"528\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/113330383\",\"caption\":\"Introducing the no CAPTCHA reCAPTCHA\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"354\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Nothing to See Here&hellip; No, Really.<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>For the second video, we were asked to visualize the concept of \\u201cinvisibility.\\u201d We brainstormed a little Rube Goldberg\\u2013esque machine to represent the complicated processes happening behind the scenes. Our motion designer, Tom, began exploring cute new ways to depict our pesky Invaders with antics like sneaking through an airport security line with a sweet \\u2018stache. A few cats started showing up as well, but that wasn\\u2019t exactly planned.<\\/p>\"}},\"529\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/166595260\",\"caption\":\"reCAPTCHA: Tough on Bots, Easy on Humans\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"355\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>One More Time, with Feeling.<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Google asked us for a third video, but the only new thing was that reCAPTCHA was available on Android API. We took this as a creative challenge and pushed the animation by introducing new Invader shenanigans.<\\/p>\"}},\"530\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/221336511\",\"caption\":\"Introducing the reCAPTCHA Android API\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"356\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The videos received nearly 2.5 million views on YouTube. But our biggest gain was the creative latitude to develop and refine our animation skills.<\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"350\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-08 20:31:54', '2017-10-08 20:31:54', 'f07ac9f1-bcd4-4dd3-be3a-b310786a5be7'),
 ('374', '360', '2', '75', 'en_us', '30', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Airbnb NYC Experiences\",\"slug\":\"airbnb-nyc-experiences\",\"postDate\":1507072500,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#ff4848\",\"63\":[\"302\"],\"4\":\"<p>We visited 5 boroughs in 4 days to help launch <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bokeh.agency\\/projects\\/airbnb-nyc-experiences#entry:360\\\">Airbnb Experiences<\\/a> in New York<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"372\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"361\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Airbnb Experiences offers classes, tours, and other activities with locals to connect visitors with their surroundings in a fresh, meaningful way. Already live in a handful of cities, Airbnb asked Bokeh to produce the multichannel launch of Airbnb Experiences in New York. Bokeh had to wing it (literally) to the Big Apple to capture unique experiences in all five boroughs in just four days.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>To create the assets&mdash;videos, content copy, b2b, PR and social images&mdash;Bokeh took our coordination skills to new heights, not only working among Airbnb\\u2019s own art, PR, social, and marketing teams, but with photographers, videographers, and models to ensure seamless timing and transitioning.<\\/p>\"}},\"362\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Services<\\/h1>\\r\\n<ul><li>Film\\/Video<\\/li><li>Photography<\\/li><li>Social<\\/li><li>Product<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"409\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/235420494\",\"caption\":\"\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"363\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>All Together Now<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>On the front end, we had to get all of the departments involved in the same room to identify individual needs and help convey the larger picture to everyone involved. After reviewing their wish lists, we consolidated them to create deliverables as smoothly and simultaneously as possible.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Then, we choreographed the production itself, prioritizing the anthem video but making sure that each photographer, videographer, and even \\u201ciPhoneagrapher\\u201d could get the shots needed fluidly and efficiently.<\\/p>\"}},\"421\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"418\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"364\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Empire State of Mind<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>For Airbnb Experiences New York, we wanted to ooze NYC vibes. We relied on bold cues, such as music and iconic New York scenes, but also incorporated a quick-cut editing style and, dynamic moving shots. To really hit that frenetic city pace, we centered the transitions on travel, including taxis, subways, and busy streets.<\\/p>\"}},\"411\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"412\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"378\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Harvest Honey with Asher\\\" Experience\"}},\"420\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"376\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Harvest Honey with Asher\\\" Experience\"}},\"413\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"381\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Be Greek with Angelis\\\" Experience\"}},\"423\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"383\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Be Greek with Angelis\\\" Experience\"}},\"422\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"395\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Design Jewelry with Dynasty and Soull\\\" Experience\"}},\"414\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"398\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Design Jewelry with Dynasty and Soull\\\" Experience\"}},\"415\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"402\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Design Jewelry with Dynasty and Soull\\\" Experience\"}},\"416\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"391\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Make a Hat with Brandon\\\" Experience\"}},\"427\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"394\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Make a Hat with Brandon\\\" Experience\"}},\"429\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"388\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Street Dance with It\'s Showtime NYC!\\\" Experience\"}},\"424\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"407\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Sail NYC History with Matt\\\" Experience\"}},\"430\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"404\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Sail NYC History with Matt\\\" Experience\"}}}}},\"365\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\"}},\"694\":{\"type\":\"threeSideBySideImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"firstImage\":[\"704\"],\"secondImage\":[\"668\"],\"thirdImage\":[\"705\"]}}},\"2\":[\"322\",\"358\",\"359\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-08 20:34:58', '2017-10-08 20:34:58', '36c17e03-5919-4c4c-8e1d-ee6684eae4c2'),
 ('375', '360', '2', '75', 'en_us', '31', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Airbnb NYC Experiences\",\"slug\":\"airbnb-nyc-experiences\",\"postDate\":1507072500,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#ff4848\",\"63\":[\"302\"],\"4\":\"<p>We visited 5 boroughs in 4 days to help launch <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bokeh.agency\\/projects\\/airbnb-nyc-experiences#entry:360:url\\\">Airbnb Experiences<\\/a> in New York<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"372\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"361\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>Since launching Trips in November 2016, Airbnb Experiences has connected travellers with classes, tours, and activities hosted by locals in a handful of cities around the world with one blaring exception: <b>New York City<\\/b>. A little under two weeks before launch, Airbnb asked Bokeh to conceptualize and execute a true multichannel production. We captured five unique experiences in each of the five boroughs in just four days of production to create assets leveraged across marketing, PR, social, and in-product. <p><\\/p>\"}},\"362\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Services<\\/h1>\\r\\n<ul><li>Film\\/Video<\\/li><li>Photography<\\/li><li>Social<\\/li><li>Product<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"409\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/235420494\",\"caption\":\"\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"363\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>All Together Now<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p><\\/p><p>On the front end, we wrangled together Airbnb\\u2019s product marketing, PR, social and art departments in the same room to help identify individual objectives, and shape the larger picture for our production. After reviewing each team\\u2019s wish list of content, we consolidated them to create an production approach that would fulfill everyone\\u2019s needs.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p> <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The production was shaped around our anthem video for product marketing. Leveraging this infrastructure, we choreographed a Camera B team to collect in-product trailers for the Airbnb app, the photographer to collect PR content, and am iPhonographer to capture vertical assets for Instagram and Instagram stories.<span><\\/span><br><\\/p>\"}},\"421\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"418\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"364\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Empire State of Mind<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>We wanted to ooze NYC vibes&mdash;for the videos that meant relying on bold cues, such as music and iconic New York scenes, as well as quick-cut editing style and dynamic movements. These exterior shots were layered with displays of genuine human connection and discovery. To capture these moments authentically, we worked with regular people (not models) and referred to them as guests at all times on set.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>However, the end goal was to show that the hosts were products of New York and the experiences were products of the hosts; these adventures could not happen anywhere else. This intent permeated through all of our work: photography included portraits of each host in their respective locations surrounded by the elements of their experiences, from bespoke hats to Greek tapas, and social media assets were shaped as \\u201ctakeovers\\u201d so the hosts could communicate to Airbnb\\u2019s audiences in a way that was both casual and captivating. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The deliverables were colorful, real and packed with sincere exploration and camaraderie. <\\/p>\\r\\n\"}},\"411\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"412\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"378\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Harvest Honey with Asher\\\" Experience\"}},\"420\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"376\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Harvest Honey with Asher\\\" Experience\"}},\"413\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"381\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Be Greek with Angelis\\\" Experience\"}},\"423\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"383\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Be Greek with Angelis\\\" Experience\"}},\"422\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"395\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Design Jewelry with Dynasty and Soull\\\" Experience\"}},\"414\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"398\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Design Jewelry with Dynasty and Soull\\\" Experience\"}},\"415\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"402\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Design Jewelry with Dynasty and Soull\\\" Experience\"}},\"416\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"391\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Make a Hat with Brandon\\\" Experience\"}},\"427\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"394\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Make a Hat with Brandon\\\" Experience\"}},\"429\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"388\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Street Dance with It\'s Showtime NYC!\\\" Experience\"}},\"424\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"407\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Sail NYC History with Matt\\\" Experience\"}},\"430\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"404\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Sail NYC History with Matt\\\" Experience\"}}}}},\"365\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\"}},\"694\":{\"type\":\"threeSideBySideImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"firstImage\":[\"704\"],\"secondImage\":[\"668\"],\"thirdImage\":[\"705\"]}}},\"2\":[\"322\",\"358\",\"359\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-08 20:56:04', '2017-10-08 20:56:04', 'a31ff2b1-b27c-4251-bc14-4b33103b9e53'),
 ('376', '367', '2', '75', 'en_us', '20', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Airbnb & Resy\",\"slug\":\"airbnb-resy\",\"postDate\":1507072860,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#00b4ae\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bokeh.agency\\/projects\\/airbnb-resy#entry:367\\\">Airbnb partnered with Resy<\\/a> to launch restaurant reservations. Things got a bit sketchy ;)<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"509\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"368\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>To make Airbnb a more functional app for users during a trip, Airbnb partnered with Resy to offer a curated list of restaurants&mdash;from local favorites to award winners&mdash;and make it easy to book a table right in the app. Bokeh was asked to develop a fun animated video to announce the launch of this new feature.<\\/p>\"}},\"524\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"695\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"369\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>You Know Me, The OG<\\/h1><p>We wanted to explore integrating the photorealistic UI of the product into the illustrated animation. This combination allowed us to actually show Resy in action on the Airbnb app, creating a video that was informative and clear, but also colorful and entertaining. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>For the animated portions, we based our color palette around green and yellow, the colors used in the app rather than Airbnb\\u2019s signature Rausch. By utilizing Kazan, Babu, and Beach, we offered a fresh take on Airbnb\\u2019s palette while still keeping it tied to the brand. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>It was also important to use an illustration style that was light and simple, with lots of lines rather than dense shapes that could conflict with the app. This directive led us to Swedish illustrator Jonas Mosesson. The resulting illustrations he did trended on Dribble\\u2019s home page for several days.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}},\"515\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"516\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"511\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"525\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"510\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"517\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"509\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"518\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"508\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"519\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"507\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"520\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"506\"],\"caption\":\"\"}}}}},\"370\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Where\\u2019s Bokeh?<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Although the video was simple, we were able to include a few Easter eggs into the design, such as including our producer\\u2019s name as one of the restaurants offered.<\\/p>\"}},\"514\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/234724566\",\"caption\":\"\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"371\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\"}}},\"2\":[\"350\",\"313\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-08 21:05:11', '2017-10-08 21:05:11', '560b4052-3e95-4e65-b5c0-4899eda2bf6e'),
 ('377', '762', '2', '75', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Airbnb Vacation Rentals\",\"slug\":\"airbnb-vacation-rentals\",\"postDate\":1507497991,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#f05b48\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p>Goat Yoga and vacation rentals. In Asheville on Airbnb.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"549\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Airbnb cofounder and CSO Nathan Blecharczyk was a keynote speaker at the Vacation Rental Managers Association national conference in Orlando, Florida. Airbnb tasked Bokeh with creating a video that conveyed Airbnb\\u2019s brand values of human connection and empathy.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Not just passing through<\\/h1><p>Airbnb has been somewhat of a dark horse in the vacation rental community and Nathan\\u2019s presentation needed to recognize that issue and connect to potential new hosts. As part of that ambition, we opted for a documentary-style film that told the story of a host and his business without relying on Airbnb talking points. We found Steve Frellick of Yonder Luxury Home Rentals in Asheville, North Carolina. Steve was on the brink of foreclosure during the recession of 2008 when his bank suggested he take one year to turn the family home he built himself into a vacation rental. He was so successful renting it on Airbnb that he now owns 80 properties. His story not only encapsulates an inherently American narrative, but his humility, passion, and empathy for his guests carries authentic emotional weight. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>From a strategic standpoint, featuring a business built in North Carolina would be culturally relevant to the audience. There are a lot of vacation rentals in the Southeast and, as the conference was in Orlando, many people attending would find personal connections to a local story.<span><\\/span><br><\\/p>\\r\\n\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>1+1=1,000,000<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>We felt Steve\\u2019s story had a heart to resonate with other vacation rental owners. Our film was a character study and a community study that aligned their interests with Airbnb\\u2019s ethos of seeking common interests and forging connections.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Throughout the narrative, Steve explains how much his business means to him and his family above and beyond financial necessity. He walks through Pine Hollow, the house he and his wife built for their family, and points out a wood beam where he used to mark his children\\u2019s heights&mdash;guests now add their heights to the same post. When people were evacuating from the hurricanes, Steve shares how he was able to help them, and, in turn, how Airbnb helped him accomplish that. These details are imperative and speak to a community focus, loving attention to detail, and a meaningful guest-host relationship; qualities that have been key Airbnb\\u2019s success.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}}},\"2\":[\"322\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-08 21:26:31', '2017-10-08 21:26:31', '42305b42-b0f3-42d6-9dbe-194c5294b66d'),
