 ('403', '28', '2', '75', 'en_us', '36', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Philz Coffee\",\"slug\":\"philz-coffee\",\"postDate\":1502594280,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#59d8d8\",\"63\":[\"698\"],\"4\":\"<p>We cold called <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bokeh.agency\\/projects\\/philz-coffee#entry:28:url\\\">Philz Coffee<\\/a> to complain about their logo, and they let us do a rebrand.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"center\",\"3\":[\"57\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"32\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Bokeh took the unconventional approach of exploring Philz\\u2019s brand identity, refreshing it, and sending a new brand deck directly to Philz\\u2019s CEO, Jacob Jaber. With custom coffee blends and a customer experience like no other, we felt that Philz deserved a brand it could fully own. The plan worked! Throughout the course of 2016, Bokeh worked intimately with the Philz team to define a uniform brand strategy that would serve as a guide for future growth. <\\/p>\"}},\"327\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Services<\\/h1>\\r\\n<ul><li>Workshops<\\/li><li>Strategy<\\/li><li>Design<\\/li><li>Brand Book & Guidelines<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"35\":{\"type\":\"inlineImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"56\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"328\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Talk it Out<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Philz need a distinct vision, mission, and set of values that could be embraced internally and expressed in every decision they made. So we conducted individual interviews, a series of leadership workshops, and a company off-site to provide safe spaces to debate ideas and tinker with concepts. <\\/p>\"}},\"329\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Trippin\\u2019 on research<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>White-space exercises and market research helped us create a profile for the typical Philz customer and to understand the perception of the Philz brand compared to that of its competitors. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Our research survey in San Francisco\\u2019s Bay Area, Los Angeles, and Washington, D.C. complemented the statistical analysis with in-person observations and on-site customer interviews.<\\/p>\"}},\"33\":{\"type\":\"quote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"quote\":\"\\\"The depth of each slide is quite impressive and on-point. I appreciate your quick-wittedness, intuition and aesthetic\\u2026 I think you know us better than we know ourselves.\\\"\",\"avatar\":[\"57\"],\"personsName\":\"Jacob Jaber\",\"jobTitle\":\"CEO\",\"shapeBackground\":[\"show\"]}},\"34\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=wxLUj1Mrars\",\"caption\":\"Caption\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"50\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The style guide<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p><em>Real<\\/em>, <em>warm<\\/em>, <em>undaunted<\\/em>, <em>relaxed<\\/em>, <em>neighborly<\\/em>, <em>light-hearted<\\/em>, and <em>unpretentious<\\/em> are the attributes infused throughout the new Philz brand identity. Starting with the logo and brand mark, we developed a custom system of colors, typography, illustrations, and iconography with guidelines.<\\/p>\"}},\"36\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"57\"],\"caption\":\"Coffee Beanz\"}},\"51\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Philz chose to pace the launch of the new branding by starting with in-store menus, wayfinding signage, and promotional newsletters.<\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"313\",\"314\",\"766\"],\"9\":\"center\"}}', '2017-10-08 21:45:29', '2017-10-08 21:45:29', 'a9a82b2c-6fa4-4263-80d4-c2226f39eb0b'),
 ('404', '360', '2', '75', 'en_us', '34', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Airbnb NYC Experiences\",\"slug\":\"airbnb-nyc-experiences\",\"postDate\":1507072500,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#ff5963\",\"63\":[\"302\"],\"4\":\"<p>We visited 5 boroughs in 4 days to help launch <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bokeh.agency\\/projects\\/airbnb-nyc-experiences#entry:360:url\\\">Airbnb Experiences<\\/a> in New York<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"372\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"361\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Since launching Trips in November 2016, Airbnb Experiences has connected travellers with classes, tours, and activities hosted by locals in a handful of cities around the world with one blaring exception: <strong>New York City<\\/strong>. A little under two weeks before launch, Airbnb asked Bokeh to conceptualize and execute a true multichannel production. We captured five unique experiences in each of the five boroughs in just four days of production to create assets leveraged across marketing, PR, social, and in-product.<\\/p>\"}},\"362\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Services<\\/h1>\\r\\n<ul><li>Film\\/Video<\\/li><li>Photography<\\/li><li>Social<\\/li><li>Product<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"409\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/235420494\",\"caption\":\"\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"363\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>All Together Now<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>On the front end, we wrangled together Airbnb\\u2019s product marketing, PR, social and art departments in the same room to help identify individual objectives, and shape the larger picture for our production. After reviewing each team\\u2019s wish list of content, we consolidated them to create an production approach that would fulfill everyone\\u2019s needs.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p> <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The production was shaped around our anthem video for product marketing. Leveraging this infrastructure, we choreographed a Camera B team to collect in-product trailers for the Airbnb app, the photographer to collect PR content, and am iPhonographer to capture vertical assets for Instagram and Instagram stories.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"421\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"418\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"364\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Empire State of Mind<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>We wanted to ooze NYC vibes&mdash;for the videos that meant relying on bold cues, such as music and iconic New York scenes, as well as quick-cut editing style and dynamic movements. These exterior shots were layered with displays of genuine human connection and discovery. To capture these moments authentically, we worked with regular people (not models) and referred to them as guests at all times on set.<br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p>However, the end goal was to show that the hosts were products of New York and the experiences were products of the hosts; these adventures could not happen anywhere else. This intent permeated through all of our work: photography included portraits of each host in their respective locations surrounded by the elements of their experiences, from bespoke hats to Greek tapas, and social media assets were shaped as \\u201ctakeovers\\u201d so the hosts could communicate to Airbnb\\u2019s audiences in a way that was both casual and captivating. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The deliverables were colorful, real and packed with sincere exploration and camaraderie. <\\/p>\"}},\"411\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"412\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"378\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Harvest Honey with Asher\\\" Experience\"}},\"420\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"376\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Harvest Honey with Asher\\\" Experience\"}},\"413\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"381\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Be Greek with Angelis\\\" Experience\"}},\"423\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"383\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Be Greek with Angelis\\\" Experience\"}},\"422\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"395\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Design Jewelry with Dynasty and Soull\\\" Experience\"}},\"414\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"398\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Design Jewelry with Dynasty and Soull\\\" Experience\"}},\"415\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"402\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Design Jewelry with Dynasty and Soull\\\" Experience\"}},\"416\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"391\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Make a Hat with Brandon\\\" Experience\"}},\"427\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"394\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Make a Hat with Brandon\\\" Experience\"}},\"429\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"388\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Street Dance with It\'s Showtime NYC!\\\" Experience\"}},\"424\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"407\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Sail NYC History with Matt\\\" Experience\"}},\"430\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"404\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Sail NYC History with Matt\\\" Experience\"}}}}},\"365\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\"}},\"694\":{\"type\":\"threeSideBySideImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"firstImage\":[\"704\"],\"secondImage\":[\"668\"],\"thirdImage\":[\"705\"]}}},\"2\":[\"322\",\"358\",\"359\",\"766\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-08 21:47:59', '2017-10-08 21:47:59', 'cd78647f-65a1-4a83-afc0-a6440abfd61b'),
 ('405', '28', '2', '75', 'en_us', '37', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Philz Coffee\",\"slug\":\"philz-coffee\",\"postDate\":1502594280,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#3eccb5\",\"63\":[\"698\"],\"4\":\"<p>We cold called <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bokeh.agency\\/projects\\/philz-coffee#entry:28:url\\\">Philz Coffee<\\/a> to complain about their logo, and they let us do a rebrand.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"center\",\"3\":[\"57\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"32\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Bokeh took the unconventional approach of exploring Philz\\u2019s brand identity, refreshing it, and sending a new brand deck directly to Philz\\u2019s CEO, Jacob Jaber. With custom coffee blends and a customer experience like no other, we felt that Philz deserved a brand it could fully own. The plan worked! Throughout the course of 2016, Bokeh worked intimately with the Philz team to define a uniform brand strategy that would serve as a guide for future growth. <\\/p>\"}},\"327\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Services<\\/h1>\\r\\n<ul><li>Workshops<\\/li><li>Strategy<\\/li><li>Design<\\/li><li>Brand Book & Guidelines<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"35\":{\"type\":\"inlineImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"56\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"328\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Talk it Out<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Philz need a distinct vision, mission, and set of values that could be embraced internally and expressed in every decision they made. So we conducted individual interviews, a series of leadership workshops, and a company off-site to provide safe spaces to debate ideas and tinker with concepts. <\\/p>\"}},\"329\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Trippin\\u2019 on research<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>White-space exercises and market research helped us create a profile for the typical Philz customer and to understand the perception of the Philz brand compared to that of its competitors. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Our research survey in San Francisco\\u2019s Bay Area, Los Angeles, and Washington, D.C. complemented the statistical analysis with in-person observations and on-site customer interviews.<\\/p>\"}},\"33\":{\"type\":\"quote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"quote\":\"\\\"The depth of each slide is quite impressive and on-point. I appreciate your quick-wittedness, intuition and aesthetic\\u2026 I think you know us better than we know ourselves.\\\"\",\"avatar\":[\"57\"],\"personsName\":\"Jacob Jaber\",\"jobTitle\":\"CEO\",\"shapeBackground\":[\"show\"]}},\"34\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/watch?v=wxLUj1Mrars\",\"caption\":\"Caption\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"50\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The style guide<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p><em>Real<\\/em>, <em>warm<\\/em>, <em>undaunted<\\/em>, <em>relaxed<\\/em>, <em>neighborly<\\/em>, <em>light-hearted<\\/em>, and <em>unpretentious<\\/em> are the attributes infused throughout the new Philz brand identity. Starting with the logo and brand mark, we developed a custom system of colors, typography, illustrations, and iconography with guidelines.<\\/p>\"}},\"36\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"57\"],\"caption\":\"Coffee Beanz\"}},\"51\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Philz chose to pace the launch of the new branding by starting with in-store menus, wayfinding signage, and promotional newsletters.<\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"313\",\"314\",\"766\"],\"9\":\"center\"}}', '2017-10-08 21:48:31', '2017-10-08 21:48:31', '63052b4a-234f-446d-9ab0-f96dd2566b4c'),
 ('406', '77', '2', '75', 'en_us', '56', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Instagram for Business\",\"slug\":\"instagram\",\"postDate\":1503364800,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#629df7\",\"63\":[\"697\"],\"4\":\"<p><strong><strong>We backpacked around the globe to shoot a series for<\\/strong>&nbsp;<\\/strong><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bokeh.agency\\/projects\\/instagram#entry:77:url\\\"><\\/a><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bokeh.agency\\/projects\\/instagram#entry:77:url\\\">Instagram<\\/a>.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"center\",\"3\":[\"235\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"282\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>The Mission<\\/h2>\\r\\n<p>In May 2016, Instagram asked Bokeh to develop the creative strategy behind its largest business marketing campaign. Over the next six months, Bokeh would trek across four continents and collaborate with twenty-four businesses in eight of Instagram\\u2019s top-performing markets to produce eight market-specific anthem films, one global anthem film, and two business profiles.<\\/p>\"}},\"283\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h2>Services<\\/h2>\\r\\n<ul><li>Concept<\\/li><li>Branding<\\/li><li>Film\\/Video<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"458\":{\"type\":\"videoCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":{\"459\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193181711\",\"caption\":\"Global Spotlight: Instagram in the UAE\"}},\"460\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193181279\",\"caption\":\"Global Spotlight: Instagram in the United Kingdom\"}},\"461\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193182109\",\"caption\":\"Global Spotlight: Instagram in Germany\"}},\"463\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193179905\",\"caption\":\"Global Spotlight: Instagram in Spain\"}},\"465\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/197975453\",\"caption\":\"Global Spotlight: Instagram in Mexico\"}},\"466\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/197975723\",\"caption\":\"Global Spotlight: Instagram in Italy\"}},\"464\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/197975916\",\"caption\":\"Global Spotlight: Instagram in Brazil\"}},\"462\":{\"type\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"video\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/193182537\",\"caption\":\"Global Spotlight: Instagram in France\"}}}}},\"323\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Nobody\\u2019s inspired by jargon<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Our creative approach was predicated on the belief that human connection is not driven by jargon or statistics. For a creative brand like Instagram, an emotional, relatable, &nbsp;and down-to-earth approach felt more powerful. Connection is not fostered by large, immobile production teams, so we strategized a plan that kept our footprint lean, our production value high, and placed a heavy value on agility. Then we tested this plan by developing a concept film and animatic.<\\/p>\"}},\"467\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/153582145\",\"caption\":\"\\\"Made on Instagram\\\" Pitch Film\",\"ratio\":\"235-1\"}},\"324\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Non-stop<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Coordinating with teams around the world put the agency on a 24-hour schedule. At one point, Bokeh was filming in three countries simultaneously.<\\/p>\"}},\"492\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"498\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"29\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"493\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"432\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"494\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"470\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"495\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"490\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"496\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"488\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"707\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"706\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"711\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"710\"],\"caption\":\"\"}}}}},\"325\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Breaking the Rules<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>By keeping the creative and production light-on-its feet we kept ourselves open to be inspired by the businesses we profiled. For Dubai Tourism we invited our partner from Instagram on a whim to \\u201caccidently\\u201d skip an afternoon of video calls to ride ATVs into the Arabian desert. This allowed us to show Dubai as multi-faceted with both urban and natural landscapes. For Mercedes-Benz we figured a down-to-earth approach did no justice for their brand. We wanted to feel the speed and energy of their vehicles so we went out to their test track in Stuttgart, and up to the skies.<\\/p>\"}},\"499\":{\"type\":\"inlineImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"497\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"326\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The assets that we created were leveraged across a variety of channels, from keynote presentations to social and Vimeo, paid media, and the Instagram for Business blog.<\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"322\",\"350\",\"766\"],\"9\":\"bottom\"}}', '2017-10-08 21:49:02', '2017-10-08 21:49:02', 'e8ab84ce-3144-4131-8a81-c1fb92e9db0d'),
 ('407', '767', '2', '75', 'en_us', '1', '', '{\"typeId\":null,\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Google Local Guides\",\"slug\":\"google-local-guides\",\"postDate\":1507499604,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#ffb500\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p><b>We did a Photo-Worthy Photoshoot for Google <\\/b><\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"544\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"new1\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Google Local Guides is a program where users leave reviews and upload photos of their favorite places so that others can find and experience them too. In September 2015, we were asked to conceptualize and produce bright and colorful photography that spoke to the values at the heart of the Local Guides brand&mdash;discovery, sharing, community.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}},\"new2\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Location, location, location<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>We started by identifying the cool local places that would resonate most with millennials (i.e. us.). We wanted to show spots slightly off the beaten path that people would be genuinely excited to share. The final list included places such as Pizzeria Delfina, Shark Fin Cove, Philz, the Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk, and Chantal Guillon Macarons.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}},\"new3\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Sharp shooter<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Photography is a tricky business. Hefty day-rates, agency fees, licensing and license renewals inflate costs and add time. They place extra burden to our partners, and keep us from working lean. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>To make our photoshoots faster, more flexible, and better suited to the digital age we developed new relationships with independent freelancers who understood the evolving media environment We also were able to maximize content output by pairing photography with active video productions and vice versa.<\\/p>\\r\\n\"}},\"new4\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p><\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"766\",\"359\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-08 21:53:24', '2017-10-08 21:53:24', '47f09640-13b4-4434-b9cd-94420b1243ce'),
 ('408', '341', '2', '75', 'en_us', '11', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Google Maps\",\"slug\":\"google-maps\",\"postDate\":1507055820,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#ffb500\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p><strong>The craziest damn video we\\u2019ve ever made for Google Maps in Turkey.<\\/strong><\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"548\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"342\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>To announce the launch of Google Streetview and the Google Maps mobile application in Turkey, Bokeh was asked to produce an inspiring anthem video. However, there was one hurdle: No map data or Streetview imagery would be accessible. To be successful, our stylistic approach had to be less reliant on the availability of digital imagery and more attached to the target market\\u2019s culture.<\\/p>\"}},\"554\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/130380842\",\"caption\":\"Google Maps: Hello Turkey\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"343\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Streetview minus the street view<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>How do you showcase a new feature without actually showing the feature? Establishing a partnership with DJI gave us the resources to shoot incredible aerial photography wherever we went. By combining this footage with hyperlapse photography and motion animation, we could mimic Satellite View in Google Maps and the user experience of moving between panoramas in Streetview.<\\/p>\"}},\"577\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/118982276\",\"caption\":\"Inspired by the DJI Inspire\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"344\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>From the Watchtower<\\/h1><p>We reached out to Leonardo Dalessandri, the Italian director of the short film Watchtower of Turkey. Watchtower captured the essence of Turkish culture; a balanced, artistic survey of Turkey\\u2019s people, customs, food, and landscapes. The video had amassed millions of views within Turkey, and from a marketing perspective incorporating Leo\\u2019s aesthetic would establish an immediate point-of-reference for users. The awe-inspiring, kinetically entrancing nature of the approach combined with Google\\u2019s reach could give the video virality.<\\/p>\"}},\"555\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"558\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"542\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"557\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"549\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"559\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"544\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"560\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"545\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"561\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"552\"],\"caption\":\"\"}}}}},\"345\":{\"type\":\"quote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"quote\":\"\\\"This is super slick. Well done all around. Never seen anything quite like this\\u2026 The transitions between the various elements are so seamless.\\\"\",\"avatar\":\"\",\"personsName\":\"Gopal Shah\",\"jobTitle\":\"Product Manager, Google Earth\",\"shapeBackground\":[\"show\"]}},\"346\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Hello Turkey<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Over the course of three weeks, we trekked across Istanbul and visited locales Izmir, Ephesus, \\u00c7e\\u015fme, and \\u015eirince.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"562\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"543\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"347\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Perhaps the most incredibly cinematic and dynamic Google Maps launch video ever made suffered the most anticlimactic of fates. Never formally released due to the political climate in Turkey.<\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"322\",\"766\",\"350\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-08 21:58:28', '2017-10-08 21:58:28', 'ea1e55d7-f237-4b6f-a564-7fbae3481561'),
 ('409', '341', '2', '75', 'en_us', '12', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Google Maps\",\"slug\":\"google-maps\",\"postDate\":1507055820,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#ffb500\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p><strong>The craziest damn video we\\u2019ve ever made for Google Maps in Turkey.<\\/strong><\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"548\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"342\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>To announce the launch of Google Streetview and the Google Maps mobile application in Turkey, Bokeh was asked to produce an inspiring anthem video. However, there was one hurdle: No map data or Streetview imagery would be accessible. To be successful, our stylistic approach had to be less reliant on the availability of digital imagery and more attached to the target market\\u2019s culture.<\\/p>\"}},\"554\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/130380842\",\"caption\":\"Google Maps: Hello Turkey\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"343\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Streetview minus the street view<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>How do you showcase a new feature without actually showing the feature? Establishing a partnership with DJI gave us the resources to shoot incredible aerial photography wherever we went. By combining this footage with hyperlapse photography and motion animation, we could mimic Satellite View in Google Maps and the user experience of moving between panoramas in Streetview.<\\/p>\"}},\"577\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/118982276\",\"caption\":\"Inspired by the DJI Inspire\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"344\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>From the Watchtower<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>We reached out to Leonardo Dalessandri, the Italian director of the short film Watchtower of Turkey. Watchtower captured the essence of Turkish culture; a balanced, artistic survey of Turkey\\u2019s people, customs, food, and landscapes. The video had amassed millions of views within Turkey, and from a marketing perspective incorporating Leo\\u2019s aesthetic would establish an immediate point-of-reference for users. The awe-inspiring, kinetically entrancing nature of the approach combined with Google\\u2019s reach could give the video virality.<\\/p>\"}},\"555\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"558\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"542\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"557\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"549\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"559\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"544\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"560\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"545\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"561\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"552\"],\"caption\":\"\"}}}}},\"345\":{\"type\":\"quote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"quote\":\"\\\"This is super slick. Well done all around. Never seen anything quite like this\\u2026 The transitions between the various elements are so seamless.\\\"\",\"avatar\":[\"772\"],\"personsName\":\"Gopal Shah\",\"jobTitle\":\"Product Manager, Google Earth\",\"shapeBackground\":[\"show\"]}},\"346\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Hello Turkey<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Over the course of three weeks, we trekked across Istanbul and visited locales Izmir, Ephesus, \\u00c7e\\u015fme, and \\u015eirince.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"562\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"543\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"347\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Perhaps the most incredibly cinematic and dynamic Google Maps launch video ever made suffered the most anticlimactic of fates. Never formally released due to the political climate in Turkey.<\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"322\",\"766\",\"350\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-08 22:02:49', '2017-10-08 22:02:49', '5451d832-747e-4168-8871-44ab9a67d810'),
 ('410', '330', '2', '75', 'en_us', '13', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Google Play\",\"slug\":\"google-play\",\"postDate\":1507055400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#59d8d8\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p>Our parents thought this Google Play April Fool\'s joke was real. Success!<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"696\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"331\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The team at Google Play was certain about two things. First, they wanted a video to commemorate the April Fool\\u2019s holiday. Second, they wanted the video to involve pets. With these parameters outlined, Bokeh went to work to develop a hilarious and entertaining video to introduce <em>Google Play for Pets<\\/em>.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"332\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Services<\\/h1>\\r\\n<ul><li>Film\\/Video<\\/li><li>Animation<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"654\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/213573065\",\"caption\":\"Google Play for Pets\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"333\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Make it believable<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>We made the conscious decision to avoid cheap laughs and cute gimmicks; to create an April Fool\\u2019s video that took itself and its intent to lead the audience astray seriously. The story&mdash;and the product at its center&mdash;had to be grounded in a real-world logic that the viewer could \\u201calmost\\u201d follow. We needed to develop a product idea that was simple, and solved a real human issue.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Our proposal: Google Play is introducing a new category of apps in the Play Store to help pet owners train their pets and keep them occupied while they\\u2019re away.<\\/p>\"}},\"655\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"658\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"644\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"657\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"634\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"659\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"643\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"661\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"635\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"662\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"651\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"656\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"641\"],\"caption\":\"\"}}}}},\"334\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>With over 1.6M views across YouTube and Facebook, <em>Google Play for Pets <\\/em>was featured as one of the top April Fool\\u2019s pranks of 2017 by publications like <strong>Adweek<\\/strong> and <strong>CNET<\\/strong>.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p><br><\\/p>\"}},\"335\":{\"type\":\"quote\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"quote\":\"\\u201cYou guys are literally amazing - thank you for dealing w\\/ this crazy last minute madness.\\\"\",\"avatar\":[\"773\"],\"personsName\":\"Meghan Lyons\",\"jobTitle\":\"Brand Marketing Manager, Google Play\",\"shapeBackground\":[\"show\"]}}},\"2\":[\"322\",\"350\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-08 22:06:12', '2017-10-08 22:06:12', 'c28bd26a-3455-42cf-a9ea-dc4cff0dd52f'),
