hy is a tricky business. Hefty day-rates, agency fees, licensing and license renewals inflate costs and add time. They place extra burden to our partners, and keep us from working lean. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>To make our photoshoots faster, more flexible, and better suited to the digital age we developed new relationships with independent freelancers who understood the evolving media environment We also were able to maximize content output by pairing photography with active video productions and vice versa.<\\/p>\"}},\"771\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The payoff<\\/h1>\"}}},\"2\":[\"766\",\"359\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-09 19:08:37', '2017-10-09 19:08:37', '057f41d2-cce2-436f-b649-2ef51006b1e2'),
 ('436', '360', '2', '75', 'en_us', '37', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Airbnb NYC Experiences\",\"slug\":\"airbnb-nyc-experiences\",\"postDate\":1507072500,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#f24733\",\"63\":[\"302\"],\"4\":\"<p>We visited 5 boroughs in 4 days to help launch <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bokeh.agency\\/projects\\/airbnb-nyc-experiences#entry:360:url\\\">Airbnb Experiences<\\/a> in New York<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"372\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"361\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Since launching Trips in November 2016, Airbnb Experiences has connected travellers with classes, tours, and activities hosted by locals in a handful of cities around the world with one blaring exception: <strong>New York City<\\/strong>. A little under two weeks before launch, Airbnb asked Bokeh to conceptualize and execute a true multichannel production. We captured five unique experiences in each of the five boroughs in just four days of production to create assets leveraged across marketing, PR, social, and in-product.<\\/p>\"}},\"362\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Services<\\/h1>\\r\\n<ul><li>Film\\/Video<\\/li><li>Photography<\\/li><li>Social<\\/li><li>Product<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"409\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/235420494\",\"caption\":\"\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"363\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>All Together Now<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>On the front end, we wrangled together Airbnb\\u2019s product marketing, PR, social and art departments in the same room to help identify individual objectives, and shape the larger picture for our production. After reviewing each team\\u2019s wish list of content, we consolidated them to create an production approach that would fulfill everyone\\u2019s needs.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p> <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The production was shaped around our anthem video for product marketing. Leveraging this infrastructure, we choreographed a Camera B team to collect in-product trailers for the Airbnb app, the photographer to collect PR content, and am iPhonographer to capture vertical assets for Instagram and Instagram stories.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"421\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"418\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"364\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Empire State of Mind<\\/h1><p>We wanted to embody the attitude and swagger of New York City. For the videos that meant paying homage with the soundtrack to New York\\u2019s jazz and hip hop culture, as well as employing a quick-cut editing style and dynamic movements. These gritty exterior shots were layered with displays of genuine human connection and discovery on the part of our guests- an authentic group of regular people (not models) who joined us on each Experience.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The end goal was to show that the hosts were products of New York and the experiences were products of the hosts; these adventures could not happen anywhere else. This intent permeated through all of our work: photography included portraits of each host in their respective locations surrounded by the elements of their experiences, from bespoke hats to Greek tapas, and social media assets were shaped as \\u201ctakeovers\\u201d so the hosts could communicate to Airbnb\\u2019s audiences in a way that was both casual and captivating. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The deliverables were colorful, real and packed with sincere exploration and camaraderie.<\\/p><p> <\\/p>\"}},\"411\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"412\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"378\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Harvest Honey with Asher\\\" Experience\"}},\"420\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"376\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Harvest Honey with Asher\\\" Experience\"}},\"413\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"381\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Be Greek with Angelis\\\" Experience\"}},\"423\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"383\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Be Greek with Angelis\\\" Experience\"}},\"422\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"395\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Design Jewelry with Dynasty and Soull\\\" Experience\"}},\"414\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"398\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Design Jewelry with Dynasty and Soull\\\" Experience\"}},\"415\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"402\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Design Jewelry with Dynasty and Soull\\\" Experience\"}},\"416\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"391\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Make a Hat with Brandon\\\" Experience\"}},\"427\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"394\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Make a Hat with Brandon\\\" Experience\"}},\"429\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"388\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Street Dance with It\'s Showtime NYC!\\\" Experience\"}},\"424\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"407\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Sail NYC History with Matt\\\" Experience\"}},\"430\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"404\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Sail NYC History with Matt\\\" Experience\"}}}}},\"365\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\"}},\"694\":{\"type\":\"threeSideBySideImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"firstImage\":[\"704\"],\"secondImage\":[\"668\"],\"thirdImage\":[\"705\"]}}},\"2\":[\"322\",\"358\",\"359\",\"766\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-09 19:12:30', '2017-10-09 19:12:30', '70479ee4-3f9c-4c0c-8949-a94f10902aef'),
 ('437', '360', '2', '75', 'en_us', '38', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Airbnb NYC Experiences\",\"slug\":\"airbnb-nyc-experiences\",\"postDate\":1507072500,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#f24733\",\"63\":[\"302\"],\"4\":\"<p>We visited 5 boroughs in 4 days to help launch <a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bokeh.agency\\/projects\\/airbnb-nyc-experiences#entry:360:url\\\">Airbnb Experiences<\\/a> in New York<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"372\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"361\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Since launching Trips in November 2016, Airbnb Experiences has connected travellers with classes, tours, and activities hosted by locals in a handful of cities around the world with one blaring exception: <strong>New York City<\\/strong>. A little under two weeks before launch, Airbnb asked Bokeh to conceptualize and execute a true multichannel production. We captured five unique experiences in each of the five boroughs in just four days of production to create assets leveraged across marketing, PR, social, and in-product.<\\/p>\"}},\"362\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Services<\\/h1>\\r\\n<ul><li>Film\\/Video<\\/li><li>Photography<\\/li><li>Social<\\/li><li>Product<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}},\"409\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/235420494\",\"caption\":\"\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"363\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>All Together Now<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>On the front end, we wrangled together Airbnb\\u2019s product marketing, PR, social and art departments in the same room to help identify individual objectives, and shape the larger picture for our production. After reviewing each team\\u2019s wish list of content, we consolidated them to create an production approach that would fulfill everyone\\u2019s needs.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p> <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The production was shaped around our anthem video for product marketing. Leveraging this infrastructure, we choreographed a Camera B team to collect in-product trailers for the Airbnb app, the photographer to collect PR content, and am iPhonographer to capture vertical assets for Instagram and Instagram stories.<br><\\/p>\"}},\"421\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"418\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"364\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Empire State of Mind<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p><\\/p><p>We wanted to embody the attitude and swagger of New York City. For the videos that meant paying homage to New York\\u2019s jazz and hip hop culture with the soundtrack, as well as employing a quick-cut editing style and dynamic movements. These gritty exterior shots were layered with displays of genuine human connection and discovery on the part of our guests&mdash;regular people (not models) who joined us on each Experience.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The end goal was to show that the hosts were products of New York and the experiences were products of the hosts; these adventures could not happen anywhere else. This intent permeated through all of our work: photography included portraits of each host in their respective locations surrounded by the elements of their experiences, from bespoke hats to Greek tapas, and social media assets were shaped as \\u201ctakeovers\\u201d so the hosts could communicate to Airbnb\\u2019s audiences in a way that was both casual and captivating. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The deliverables were colorful, real and packed with sincere exploration and camaraderie.<span><\\/span><br><\\/p>\\r\\n<p> <\\/p>\"}},\"411\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"412\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"378\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Harvest Honey with Asher\\\" Experience\"}},\"420\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"376\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Harvest Honey with Asher\\\" Experience\"}},\"413\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"381\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Be Greek with Angelis\\\" Experience\"}},\"423\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"383\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Be Greek with Angelis\\\" Experience\"}},\"422\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"395\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Design Jewelry with Dynasty and Soull\\\" Experience\"}},\"414\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"398\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Design Jewelry with Dynasty and Soull\\\" Experience\"}},\"415\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"402\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Design Jewelry with Dynasty and Soull\\\" Experience\"}},\"416\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"391\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Make a Hat with Brandon\\\" Experience\"}},\"427\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"394\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Make a Hat with Brandon\\\" Experience\"}},\"429\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"388\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Street Dance with It\'s Showtime NYC!\\\" Experience\"}},\"424\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"407\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Sail NYC History with Matt\\\" Experience\"}},\"430\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"404\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Sail NYC History with Matt\\\" Experience\"}}}}},\"365\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\"}},\"694\":{\"type\":\"threeSideBySideImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"firstImage\":[\"704\"],\"secondImage\":[\"668\"],\"thirdImage\":[\"705\"]}}},\"2\":[\"322\",\"358\",\"359\",\"766\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-09 20:21:14', '2017-10-09 20:21:14', 'a82e1cca-7def-47bf-9d6f-d54eb74d7b20'),
 ('438', '367', '2', '75', 'en_us', '25', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Airbnb & Resy\",\"slug\":\"airbnb-resy\",\"postDate\":1507072860,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#00b4ae\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p><a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/bokeh.agency\\/projects\\/airbnb-resy#entry:367:url\\\">Airbnb partnered with Resy<\\/a> to launch restaurant reservations. Things got a bit sketchy&nbsp;\\ud83d\\ude09<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"509\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"368\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>To make Airbnb a more functional app for users during a trip, Airbnb partnered with Resy to offer a curated list of restaurants&mdash;from local favorites to award winners&mdash;and make it easy to book a table right in the app. Bokeh was asked to develop a fun animated video to announce the launch of this new feature.<\\/p>\"}},\"524\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"695\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"369\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Swede and simple<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>We wanted to explore integrating the photorealistic UI of the product into the illustrated animation. This combination allowed us to actually show Resy in action on the Airbnb app, creating a video that was informative and clear, but also colorful and entertaining. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>For the animated portions, we based our color palette around green and yellow, the colors used in the app rather than Airbnb\\u2019s signature Rausch. By utilizing Kazan, Babu, and Beach, we offered a fresh take on Airbnb\\u2019s palette while still keeping it tied to the brand. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>It was also important to use an illustration style that was light and simple, with lots of lines rather than dense shapes that could conflict with the app. This directive led us to Swedish illustrator Jonas Mosesson. The resulting illustrations he did trended on Dribble\\u2019s home page for several days.<\\/p>\"}},\"515\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"516\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"511\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"525\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"510\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"517\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"509\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"518\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"508\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"519\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"507\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"520\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"506\"],\"caption\":\"\"}}}}},\"370\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Where\\u2019s Bokeh?<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Although the video was simple, we were able to include a few Easter eggs into the design, such as including our producer\\u2019s name as one of the restaurants offered.<\\/p>\"}},\"514\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/234724566\",\"caption\":\"\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"371\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\"}}},\"2\":[\"350\",\"313\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-09 20:22:04', '2017-10-09 20:22:04', '81a8f2be-ff0e-4cd8-a60a-4df599ddf661'),
 ('439', '767', '2', '75', 'en_us', '10', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Google Local Guides\",\"slug\":\"google-local-guides\",\"postDate\":1507499580,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#f4ac1b\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p><strong>We did a Photo-Worthy Photoshoot for Google <\\/strong><\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"779\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"768\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Google Local Guides is a program where users leave reviews and upload photos of their favorite places so that others can find and experience them too. In September 2015, we were asked to conceptualize and produce bright and colorful photography that spoke to the values at the heart of the Local Guides brand&mdash;discovery, sharing, community.<\\/p>\"}},\"809\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"807\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"769\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Location, location, location<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>We started by identifying the cool local places that would resonate most with millennials (i.e. us.). We wanted to show spots slightly off the beaten path that people would be genuinely excited to share. The final list included places such as Pizzeria Delfina, Shark Fin Cove, Philz, the Santa Cruz Beach Boardwalk, and Chantal Guillon Macarons.<\\/p>\"}},\"801\":{\"type\":\"imageCarousel\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":{\"803\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"815\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"802\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"811\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"804\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"813\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"805\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"812\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"806\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"810\"],\"caption\":\"\"}}}}},\"770\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Sharp shooter<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Photography is a tricky business. Hefty day-rates, agency fees, licensing and license renewals inflate costs and add time. They place extra burden to our partners, and keep us from working lean. <\\/p>\\r\\n<p>To make our photoshoots faster, more flexible, and better suited to the digital age we developed new relationships with independent freelancers who understood the evolving media environment We also were able to maximize content output by pairing photography with active video productions and vice versa.<\\/p>\"}},\"771\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The payoff<\\/h1>\"}}},\"2\":[\"766\",\"359\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-09 20:38:38', '2017-10-09 20:38:38', 'ccc78fe1-3797-4f38-8550-3197f6ae7f06'),
 ('440', '351', '2', '75', 'en_us', '19', '', '{\"typeId\":\"2\",\"authorId\":\"75\",\"title\":\"Google reCAPTCHA\",\"slug\":\"google-recaptcha\",\"postDate\":1507056060,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":null,\"fields\":{\"6\":\"#42e161\",\"63\":\"\",\"4\":\"<p>We found a way to make Google security software adorable. Three times.<\\/p>\",\"8\":\"left\",\"3\":[\"585\"],\"5\":\"\",\"10\":{\"352\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Mission<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>To create and evolve a series of colorful, entertaining animated videos that could visualize Google\\u2019s reCAPTCHA, a technical online security product for verifying a user\\u2019s identity that\\u2019s engineered to be less noticeable.<\\/p>\"}},\"534\":{\"type\":\"inlineImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"537\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"353\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Gotta CAPTCHA All<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>CAPTCHA is the virtual door that exists between you and the thing you really want to do&mdash;like make a safe and secure online purchase. But CAPTCHA lives completely in a digital world. We decided that an animated approach would be the easiest way to help people understand the technology. To keep things intelligible, but relatable, we borrowed the 8-bit Space Invader characters used on the reCAPTCHA website to represent malicious malware. We never gave them back&mdash;the Invaders became a major motif in the following videos. <\\/p>\"}},\"528\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/113330383\",\"caption\":\"Introducing the no CAPTCHA reCAPTCHA\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"354\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>Nothing to See Here&hellip; No, Really.<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>For the second video, we were asked to visualize the concept of \\u201cinvisibility.\\u201d We brainstormed a little Rube Goldberg\\u2013esque machine to represent the complicated processes happening behind the scenes. Our motion designer, Tom, began exploring cute new ways to depict our pesky Invaders with antics like sneaking through an airport security line with a sweet \\u2018stache. A few cats started showing up as well, but that wasn\\u2019t exactly planned.<\\/p>\"}},\"529\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/166595260\",\"caption\":\"reCAPTCHA: Tough on Bots, Easy on Humans\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"355\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>One More Time, with Feeling.<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>Google asked us for a third video, but the only new thing was that reCAPTCHA was available on Android API. We took this as a creative challenge and pushed the animation by introducing new Invader shenanigans.<\\/p>\"}},\"530\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/221336511\",\"caption\":\"Introducing the reCAPTCHA Android API\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"356\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\\r\\n<p>The videos received nearly 2.5 million views on YouTube. But our biggest gain was the creative latitude to develop and refine our animation skills.<\\/p>\"}}},\"2\":[\"350\",\"313\"],\"9\":\"top\"}}', '2017-10-09 20:40:05', '2017-10-09 20:40:05', '7fc7a1a5-bdcb-4944-a74d-cef803b5dd1b'),
