sty and Soull\\\" Experience\"}},\"416\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"391\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Make a Hat with Brandon\\\" Experience\"}},\"427\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"394\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Make a Hat with Brandon\\\" Experience\"}},\"429\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"388\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Street Dance with It\'s Showtime NYC!\\\" Experience\"}},\"424\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"407\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Sail NYC History with Matt\\\" Experience\"}},\"430\":{\"type\":\"2\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"404\"],\"caption\":\"Still from the \\\"Sail NYC History with Matt\\\" Experience\"}}}}},\"871\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<p>The end goal was to show that the hosts were products of New York and the experiences were products of the hosts; these adventures could not happen anywhere else. This intent permeated through all of our work: photography included portraits of each host in their respective locations surrounded by the elements of their experiences, from bespoke hats to Greek tapas, and social media assets were shaped as \\u201ctakeovers\\u201d so the hosts could communicate to Airbnb\\u2019s audiences in a way that was both casual and captivating.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The deliverables were colorful, real and packed with sincere exploration and camaraderie.<\\/p>\"}},\"694\":{\"type\":\"threeSideBySideImages\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"firstImage\":[\"861\"],\"secondImage\":[\"816\"],\"thirdImage\":[\"862\"]}},\"365\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"copy\":\"<h1>The Payoff<\\/h1>\"}},\"866\":{\"type\":\"video\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"videoUrl\":\"https:\\/\\/vimeo.com\\/238996472\",\"caption\":\"Airbnb NYC Experiences 30s TV Spot\",\"ratio\":\"16-9\"}},\"1027\":{\"type\":\"fullWidthImage\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"image\":[\"1026\"],\"caption\":\"\"}},\"864\":{\"type\":\"inlineIm